 Open \u2013 Doubles|{{dts|Mar 2018}}]]\n|[[Brasil Open]], Brazil\n|250 Series\n|Clay (i)\n|{{flagicon|NED}} Wesley Koolhof\n|{{flagicon|ARG}} [[Federico Delbonis]]<br>{{flagicon|ARG}} [[M\u00e1ximo Gonz\u00e1lez]]\n|4\u20136, 2\u20136\n|-\n|bgcolor=FFA07A|Loss\n|<small>3\u20137</small>\n|[[2018 Estoril Open \u2013 Doubles|{{dts|May 2018}}]]\n|[[Estoril Open (tennis)|Estoril Open]], Portugal\n|250 Series\n|Clay\n|{{flagicon|NED}} Wesley Koolhof\n|{{flagicon|GBR}} [[Kyle Edmund]]<br>{{flagicon|GBR}} [[Cameron Norrie]]\n|4\u20136, 2\u20136\n|-\n|bgcolor=98FB98|Win\n|<small>4\u20137</small>\n|[[2018 Hall of Fame Tennis Championships \u2013 Doubles|{{dts|Jul 2018}}]]\n|[[Hall of Fame Open]], United States\n|250 Series\n|Grass\n|{{flagicon|ISR}} [[Jonathan Erlich]]\n|{{flagicon|ESA}} [[Marcelo Ar\u00e9valo]]<br>{{flagicon|MEX}} [[Miguel \u00c1ngel Reyes-Varela]]\n|6\u20131, 6\u20132\n|-\n|bgcolor=FFA07A|Loss\n|<small>4\u20138</small>\n|[[2019 Abierto Mexicano Telcel \u2013 Men's Doubles|{{dts|Mar 2019}}]]\n|style=\"background:#d4f1c5;\"|[[Mexican Open (tennis)|Mexican Open]], Mexico\n|style=\"background:#d4f1c5;\"|500 Series\n|Hard\n|{{flagicon|USA}} [[Austin Krajicek]]\n|{{flagicon|GER}} [[Alexander Zverev]]<br>{{flagicon|GER}} [[Mischa Zverev]]\n|6\u20132, 6\u20137<sup>(4\u20137)</sup>, [5\u201310]\n|-\n|bgcolor=98FB98|Win\n|<small>5\u20138</small>\n|[[2019 Antalya Open \u2013 Doubles|{{dts|Jun 2019}}]]\n|[[Antalya Open]], Turkey\n|250 Series\n|Grass\n|{{flagicon|ISR}} Jonathan Erlich\n|{{flagicon|CRO}} [[Ivan Dodig]]<br>{{flagicon|SVK}} [[Filip Pol\u00e1\u0161ek]]\n|6\u20133, 6\u20134\n|}\n\n==ATP Challenger and ITF Futures finals==\n\n===Singles: 17 (5 titles, 12 runners-up)===\n{|\n|-valign=top\n|\n{|class=wikitable style=font-size:97%\n!Legend\n|-bgcolor=moccasin\n|ATP Challenger (0\u20130)\n|-bgcolor=cffcff\n|ITF Futures (5\u201312)\n|}\n|\n{|class=wikitable style=font-size:97%\n!Finals by surface\n|-\n|Hard (4\u20138)\n|-\n|Clay (1\u20134)\n|-\n|Grass (0\u20130)\