    = 10\n|label-color4      = black\n| mark-coord4      = {{coord|44.9274|-63.5366}}\n|mark-title4       = [[Enfield, Nova Scotia]]\n}}\n| partof           = \n| image            = \n| image_size       = \n| alt              = \n| caption          = \n| map              = \n| map_size         = \n| map_alt          = \n| map_caption      = Portapique in Nova Scotia\n| susperp          = \n| location         = [[Nova Scotia]], Canada\n| target           = \n| date             = {{start date|2020|4|18}}\u2013{{end date|2020|4|19}}\n| time             = \n| timezone         = [[UTC\u221203:00]]\n| coordinates      = \n| type             = [[Spree killer|Spree shooting]], [[mass shooting]],<ref name=\"Vox\" /> [[arson]]\n| weapons          = Firearm(s)\n| fatalities       = At least 19 (including the perpetrator)<ref name=\"CBC3\"/>\n| injuries         = At least 2<ref name=\"CBC3\"/>\n| victim           = \n| perp             = Gabriel Wortman\n| numparts         = \n| numpart          = \n| dfens            = \n| dfen             = \n| footage          = \n| motive           = Under investigation\n}}\n\nOn April 18 and April 19, 2020, Gabriel Wortman killed at least 18 people and set fire to at least five buildings in the [[Canadian province]] of [[Nova Scotia]] before being killed by the [[RCMP]] following a vehicle pursuit.<ref name=\"CBC4\">{{cite news|url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/nova-scotia/mass-killing-shooting-victims-remembered-1.5538032|title=Teacher, family of 3 and RCMP officer among victims of N.S. shooting rampage|publisher=CBC News|accessdate=April 20, 2020|date=April 19, 2020}}</ref>\n\nIt is the deadliest attack involving the use of firearms in Canadian history, surpassing the 1989 [[\u00c9cole Polytechnique massacre]], during which 15 people were killed.<ref name=\"AP\">{{cite news|url=https://apnews.com/7c9a33ae52420e0ddbfb5275898a7e79|title=16 killed in shooting rampage, deadliest in Canadian history|last=Gillies|first=Rob|publisher=Associated Press|accessdate=April 19, 2020|date=April 19, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200419202425/https://apnews.com/7c9a33ae52420e0ddbfb5275898a7e79|archive-date=April 19, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Police say the motive has not yet been established.<ref name=\"nyt-nova-scotia-shooting-gabriel-wortman\">{{Cite news|last=Diaz|first=Johnny|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/04/19/world/canada/nova-scotia-shooting-gabriel-wortman.html|title=Nova Scotia Shooting Kills at Least 16, Police Say|date=April 19, 2020|newspaper=[[The New York Times]]|access-date=April 19, 2020|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200419142013/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/04/19/world/canada/nova-scotia-shooting-gabriel-wortman.html|archive-date=April 19, 2020|last2=Bilefsky|first2=Dan}}</ref><ref name=\"Politico\">{{cite news|last=Blatchford|first=Andy|url=https://www.politico.com/news/2020/04/19/at-least-10-dead-in-canadian-shooting-rampage-195506|title=Gunman kills at least 16, including officer, in Nova Scotia|date=April 19, 2020|accessdate=April 20, 2020|publisher=Politico}}</ref>\n\n==Timeline==\nOn April 18, at around 11:00 p.m. [[Atlantic Time Zone|ADT]], [[Royal Canadian Mounted Police]] (RCMP) officers responded to multiple [[9-1-1]] calls regarding a gun-related incident in the community of [[Portapique]], {{convert|130|km|mi}} north of [[Halifax, Nova Scotia|Halifax]].<ref name=\"CBC3\">{{cite news|url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/nova-scotia/mass-killings-what-we-know-what-we-don-t-1.5537918|title=Nova Scotia mass killings: What we know and what we don't know|date=April 19, 2020|accessdate=April 19, 2020|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200420034520/https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/nova-scotia/mass-killings-what-we-know-what-we-don-t-1.5537918|archive-date=April 20, 2020|publisher=CBC News}}</ref><ref name=\"nyt-nova-scotia-shooting-gabriel-wortman\" /><ref name=\"CBC2\">{{cite news|url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/nova-scotia/nova-scotia-timeline-active-shooter-portapique-1.5537756|title=Timeline: How an active-shooter situation unfolded in Nova Scotia|date=April 19, 2020|accessdate=April 19, 2020|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200420001136/https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/nova-scotia/nova-scotia-timeline-active-shooter-portapique-1.5537756|archive-date=April 20, 2020|publisher=CBC News}}</ref><ref name=\"NBC\">{{cite news|last1=Madani|first1=Doha|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/world/canadian-authorities-say-mass-shooting-suspect-may-have-been-disguised-n1187381|title=16 dead, including officer, in shooting, Canadian authorities say|date=April 19, 2020|accessdate=April 19, 2020|publisher=NBC News|last2=Stelloh|first2=Tim}}</ref> Three houses on Portapique Beach Road were found on fire, and at least five victims were located; they were \"gunned down as they tried to escape the flames.\" One of the first officers to respond to the scene reported by radio that they had yet to locate an armed suspect, and that \"it's very bad what's going on down here.\"<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite news|last=Tasker|first=John Paul|url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/politics/nova-scotia-tick-tock-murder-rampage-1.5539000|title='Those scars will never heal': piecing together a gunman's murderous rampage in Nova Scotia|date=April 20, 2020|work=CBC News|access-date=April 21, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"ABC\">{{cite news|last=Deliso|first=Meredith|url=https://abcnews.go.com/International/multiple-victims-canada-shooting-suspect-dressed-police-officer/story?id=70232582|title=16 dead, including police officer, in deadliest shooting in Canadian history|date=April 19, 2020|accessdate=April 19, 2020|publisher=ABC News}}</ref>\n\nAt 11:32 p.m., the RCMP sent a [[Twitter|tweet]] asking residents of the area to stay inside with their doors locked, but no message was sent through the provincial [[Emergency Alert System|emergency alert system]]. The investigation developed overnight, and by the morning of April 19, police said they were dealing with an [[active shooter]] situation.<ref name=\"CBC3\" /><ref name=\"nyt-nova-scotia-shooting-gabriel-wortman\" /><ref name=\"CBC2\" /><ref name=\"MassLive\">{{cite news|url=https://www.masslive.com/news/2020/04/nova-scotia-shooting-gabriel-wortman-kills-16-including-police-officer-in-canadas-deadliest-shooting-attack.html|title=Nova Scotia shooting: Gabriel Wortman kills 16 including police officer in Canada's deadliest shooting attack|date=April 19, 2020|accessdate=April 19, 2020|publisher=MassLive}}</ref>\n\nAt around 8:00 a.m., a 9-1-1 caller reported \"an explosion and gunfire\" at a house on Hunter Road in [[Wentworth, Nova Scotia|Wentworth]], approximately {{convert|37|km|mi}} north of Portapique. The two residents were killed, as was a neighbour who went to render assistance. Another victim was then shot and killed while walking in the community of [[Wentworth Valley]], on the road back south to Portapique.<ref name=\"CBC4\" />\n\nRCMP identified Wortman, age 51, as the suspect at 8:54 a.m., and warned that he was [[Police impersonation|dressed as an RCMP officer and operating a replica police vehicle]].<ref name=\"CBC2\" /><ref name=\"CTV\">{{cite news|last=Jerrett|first=Andrea|url=https://atlantic.ctvnews.ca/nova-scotia-shooting-suspect-shot-and-killed-by-police-1.4902687|title=At least 18 people killed in N.S. shooting; deadliest such attack in Canada: police|date=April 19, 2020|accessdate=April 19, 2020|publisher=CTV News}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Shah|first=Maryam|url=https://globalnews.ca/news/6840120/nova-scotia-shooting-timeline/|title=Timeline: What we know about the Nova Scotia shooting spree|date=April 19, 2020|accessdate=April 19, 2020|publisher=Global News}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ctvnews.ca/canada/a-timeline-of-the-deadly-shooting-incident-in-nova-scotia-1.4902954|title=A timeline of the deadly shooting incident in Nova Scotia|last1=Neustaeter|first1=Brooklyn|last2=Lopez-Martinez|first2=Melissa|date=April 19, 2020|website=CTV News|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200420053707/https://www.ctvnews.ca/canada/a-timeline-of-the-deadly-shooting-incident-in-nova-scotia-1.4902954|archive-date=April 20, 2020|access-date=April 19, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"CBC\">{{cite news|url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/nova-scotia/rcmp-weapon-lockdown-portapique-1.5537598|title=RCMP officer among the dead after Nova Scotia gunman's rampage|date=April 19, 2020|accessdate=April 19, 2020|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200419130936/https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/nova-scotia/rcmp-weapon-lockdown-portapique-1.5537598|archive-date=April 19, 2020|publisher=CBC News}}</ref> Between 10:04 and 11:04 a.m., he was sighted in or near the communities of [[Glenholme]], [[Debert]], and [[Brookfield, Nova Scotia|Brookfield]], indicating he was travelling south along [[Nova Scotia Highway 102|Highway 102]] toward Halifax.<ref name=\":2\" /> A law enforcement source told [[CNN]] that during this time, Wortman began randomly pulling drivers over and killing them.<ref name=\"CNN\" />\n\nSometime shortly before 11:24 a.m., Wortman encountered RCMP Constable Heidi Stevenson along [[Nova Scotia Trunk 2|Highway 2]], in the community of [[Shubenacadie, Nova Scotia|Shubenacadie]]. Witnesses reported seeing Wortman run towards Stevenson and hearing an exchange of gunfire, which killed Stevenson and injured another officer.<ref name=\"CBC\" /> Two burning cars were observed at the scene, including an RCMP cruiser which may have been Wortman's replica.<ref name=\"CBC6\">{{cite news|url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/nova-scotia/mass-killings-shooting-community-reaction-1.5538181|title=Death toll from Nova Scotia gunman's rampage climbs to 19|date=April 20, 2020|accessdate=April 20, 2020|publisher=CBC News}}</ref> Thereafter, he continued south in a silver [[Chevrolet Tracker (Americas)|Chevrolet Tracker]] [[Sport utility vehicle|SUV]] stolen from one of his victims, and he was next seen in [[Milford (Halifax), Nova Scotia|Milford]].<ref name=\"CBC2\" /><ref name=\"BBC\">{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-52346447|title=Canada shooting: Gunman kills at least 18 in Nova Scotia|date=April 19, 2020|accessdate=April 19, 2020|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200419211041/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-52346447|archive-date=April 19, 2020|publisher=BBC News}}</ref>\n\nFinally, at 11:40 a.m., over 12 hours after police responded to the first firearms complaint, Wortman was shot and killed by police at the [[Irving Oil|Irving]] Big Stop gas station in [[Enfield, Nova Scotia|Enfield]], about {{convert|92|km|mi}} south of Portapique and about {{convert|40|km|mi}} north of Halifax.<ref name=\"Vox\">{{cite news|last=Collins|first=Sean|url=https://www.vox.com/world/2020/4/19/21227349/mass-shooting-nova-scotia-canada-enfield-portapique|title=What we know about a mass shooting in Nova Scotia, Canada|date=April 19, 2020|accessdate=April 19, 2020|publisher=Vox}}</ref><ref name=\"CBC2\" /><ref name=\"CTV\" />\n\n==Investigation==\nNo official motive has been established for the rampage, which is not considered an act of [[Terrorism in Canada|terrorism]].<ref name=\"nyt-nova-scotia-shooting-gabriel-wortman\" />\n\nOn the afternoon of April 20, RCMP Chief Superintendent Chris Leather said there were 16 crime scenes in total, including five structure fires, which were scattered over a distance of at least {{convert|50|km|mi}}. He said he expected the death toll to rise as these crime scenes are investigated further.<ref name=\"CBC6\" />\n\nCiting an unnamed law enforcement source, CNN reported that the incident may have begun as a case of domestic violence at one of the homes in Portapique, where Wortman was allegedly trying to find a former partner.<ref name=\"CNN\" />\n\n[[Nova Scotia]]'s [[Serious Incident Response Team]] announced it would conduct an investigation into the officer-involved shooting, as well as a second police use-of-force incident.<ref name=\"CBC\" /><ref name=\"CBC6\" /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://sirt.novascotia.ca/investigation-begins-enfield-death|title=INVESTIGATION BEGINS INTO ENFIELD DEATH|publisher=Serious Incident Response Team|date=April 19, 2020|accessdate=April 20, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://sirt.novascotia.ca/sirt-investigate-discharge-firearm-rcmp-officers|title=SIRT TO INVESTIGATE DISCHARGE OF FIREARM BY RCMP OFFICERS|publisher=Serious Incident Response Team|date=April 20, 2020|accessdate=April 20, 2020}}</ref>\n\nQuestions were raised about why Nova Scotia did not use its [[emergency alert system]] to warn the public about the killings. The RCMP used Twitter to provide updates, but the areas affected had poor Internet service and were mostly populated by seniors who might not use social media. Usage of Nova Scotia's emergency alert system would have sent text messages advising residents of what was happening and to stay indoors. Superintendent Leather said an investigation would be conducted into the decision-making process to alert the public.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/nova-scotia/ns-public-alert-1.5538286|title=N.S. premier not ready to question if a public alert should have been issued about gunman|publisher=CBC News|last=Gorman|first=Michael|date=April 20, 2020|accessdate=April 20, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Victims==\nWortman killed at least 18 people, one of them RCMP Constable Heidi Stevenson, a 23-year veteran. He shot and wounded a second RCMP officer, who is in stable condition.<ref name=\"CBC3\"/><ref name=\"CBC\" /><ref name=\"global-news-rcmp-active-shooter-portapique-n-s\">{{Cite news|last=Quon|first=Alexander|url=https://globalnews.ca/news/6838880/rcmp-active-shooter-portapique-n-s/|title=17 dead, including one RCMP officer, after shooting spree in Portapique, N.S.|date=April 19, 2020|access-date=April 19, 2020|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200419202613/https://globalnews.ca/news/6838880/rcmp-active-shooter-portapique-n-s/|archive-date=April 19, 2020|publisher=[[Global News]]|last2=Stephenson|first2=Mercedes}}</ref> At least one other person was injured.<ref name=\"CBC3\" /> According to Commissioner [[Brenda Lucki]], some of his first victims were closely connected to him, but as he continued, his targets became more random.<ref name=\"nyt-nova-scotia-shooting-gabriel-wortman\" /> The dead are believed to have died from gunshot wounds, but other causes are also being investigated.<ref name=\"CBC3\" /><ref name=\"BBC\" /> The RCMP expects to find more bodies within the remnants of five structure fires.<ref name=\"CTV4\">{{cite web|url=https://www.ctvnews.ca/canada/nova-scotia-rampage-results-in-18-victims-16-crime-scenes-1.4903398|title=Nova Scotia rampage results in 18 victims, 16 crime scenes|date=April 20, 2020|work=[[CTV News]]|first=Meredith|last=MacLeod|accessdate=April 20, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Perpetrator==\nThe RCMP identified the perpetrator as Gabriel Wortman, a [[denturist]] working in the Halifax area. He owned real estate in Portapique and [[Dartmouth, Nova Scotia|Dartmouth]].<ref name=\"CBC\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/apr/20/nova-scotia-shooting-gunman-profile-quiet-gentle-denturist|title=Nova Scotia shooting: shock and surprise at killings by denturist|first=Leyland|last=Cecco|date=April 19, 2020|accessdate=April 19, 2020|website=The Guardian}}</ref> He attended [[Riverview High School (New Brunswick)|Riverview High School]] in New Brunswick and aspired to be a police officer.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://atlantic.ctvnews.ca/just-unbelievable-neighbours-of-nova-scotia-shooting-suspect-shocked-by-news-1.4903021|title='Just unbelievable': Neighbours of Nova Scotia shooting suspect shocked by news|date=April 19, 2020|website=CTV News|language=en|access-date=April 20, 2020}}</ref> Acquaintances described him as a house-proud and polite man who often spent time at a seasonal home near [[Cobequid Bay]].<ref name=\"CTV5\">{{cite news|url=https://www.ctvnews.ca/canada/what-we-know-about-the-nova-scotia-rampage-suspect-1.4903920|title=What we know about the Nova Scotia rampage suspect|publisher=CTV News|last=Bogart|first=Nicole|date=April 20, 2020|accessdate=April 20, 2020}}</ref>\n\nWortman had a hobby of buying law enforcement memorabilia and refurbishing old police cruisers. One person called his home a \"shrine\" for the RCMP.<ref name=\":0\">{{cite news|url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/canada/article-nova-scotia-mass-shooter-was-a-denturist-with-an-obsession-for/|title=Nova Scotia mass shooter was a denturist with an obsession for policing|publisher=The Globe and Mail|last1=Woo|first1=Andrew|last2=Mercer|first2=Greg|date=April 19, 2020|accessdate=April 20, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200420055810/https://www.theglobeandmail.com/canada/article-nova-scotia-mass-shooter-was-a-denturist-with-an-obsession-for/|archive-date=April 20, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> He stored the two old police cruisers that he bought behind his dental clinic.<ref name=\":1\" /><ref name=\"CTV5\" />\n\nNeighbours said Wortman struggled with [[alcohol use]] and his profitable business was impacted by the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Nova Scotia|coronavirus pandemic]], which forced all non-essential dental services to cease.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n==Reactions==\nFlags across Canada were lowered to [[half-mast]],<ref name=\"Guardian2\">{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/apr/20/nova-scotia-shooting-friends-family-pay-tribute-victims|title=Nova Scotia shooting: friends and family pay tribute to 'beautiful souls' lost in rampage|publisher=The Guardian|last=Cecco|first=Leyland|date=April 20, 2020|accessdate=April 20, 2020}}</ref> and the [[House of Commons of Canada|House of Commons]] observed a moment of silence for the victims.<ref>{{cite web| url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/politics/trudeau-nova-scotia-shooting-1.5538301| title='We're going to get through this together': Trudeau calls for unity after mass killing| website=CBC News| date=April 20, 2020| accessdate=April 20, 2020| url-status=live| archive-url=http://archive.is/7qFSQ| archive-date=April 20, 2020}}</ref>\n\n[[Nova Scotia Premier]] [[Stephen McNeil]] told reporters, \"This is one of the most senseless acts of violence in our province's history.\" He expressed his condolences to the residents affected and the families of the victims.<ref name=\"CTV2\">{{cite news|url=https://atlantic.ctvnews.ca/shooting-one-of-the-most-senseless-acts-of-violence-in-nova-scotia-s-history-premier-1.4902917|title=Shooting 'one of the most senseless acts of violence' in Nova Scotia's history: premier|last=Jerrett|first=Andrea|publisher=CTV News|accessdate=April 19, 2020|date=April 19, 2020}}</ref> \n\nCanadian Prime Minister [[Justin Trudeau]] also expressed his condolences.<ref name=\"CBC\" /> During his morning address from [[Rideau Cottage]] on April 20, he reaffirmed his commitment to strengthening gun control.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ctvnews.ca/politics/trudeau-reiterates-gun-control-commitment-in-wake-of-mass-shooting-1.4903966|title=Trudeau reiterates gun control commitment in wake of mass shooting|publisher=CTV News|last=Gilmore|first=Rachel|date=April 20, 2020|accessdate=April 20, 2020}}</ref> Trudeau also asked the media to avoid so much as mentioning Wortman's name or publishing a photograph of him. \"Do not give this person the gift of infamy\", Trudeau said.<ref name=name>{{cite news|url=https://www.macleans.ca/opinion/the-killers-name/|author=Terry Glavin|title=The killer's name|publisher=''Maclean's''|date=20 April 2020|accessdate=21 April 2020]</ref> \n\nThe [[White House]] condemned the killings and expressed US President [[Donald Trump]] and First Lady [[Melania Trump]]'s condolences.<ref name=\"CNN\">{{cite news|url=https://www.cnn.com/2020/04/20/americas/nova-scotia-shooting-monday/index.html|title=Gunman evaded police for nearly 12 hours and killed at least 18 in one of Canada's deadliest mass shootings|publisher=CNN|last1=McLaughlin|first1=Eliott C.|last2=Newton|first2=Paula|date=April 20, 2020|accessdate=April 20, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[Moncton shooting]]\n* [[List of massacres in Canada]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:2020 crimes in Canada]]\n[[Category:2020 in Nova Scotia]]\n[[Category:2020 mass shootings]]\n[[Category:2020 mass shootings in North America]]\n[[Category:2020 murders in North America]]\n[[Category:2020s mass shootings in North America]]\n[[Category:21st-century mass murder in North America]]\n[[Category:April 2020 crimes]]\n[[Category:April 2020 events in Canada]]\n[[Category:Arson in Canada]]\n[[Category:Arson in the 2020s]]\n[[Category:Attacks on buildings and structures in 2020]]\n[[Category:Crime in Nova Scotia]]\n[[Category:Death in Nova Scotia]]\n[[Category:Deaths by firearm in Canada]]\n[[Category:Mass shootings in Canada]]\n[[Category:Mass murder in Canada]]\n[[Category:Royal Canadian Mounted Police]]\n[[Category:Spree shootings in Canada]]\n", "text_old": "<noinclude>{{User:RMCD bot/subject notice|1=2020 Nova Scotia attacks|2=Talk:Nova Scotia killings#Requested move 20 April 2020 }}\n</noinclude>{{pp-move-dispute|small=yes}}\n{{short description|Series of killings in Nova Scotia, Canada}}\n{{Authority control}}\n{{Current|date=April 2020}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Use Canadian English|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox civilian attack\n| title            = Nova Scotia killings\n{{OSM Location map\n| coord            = {{coord|45.1965|-63.3377}}\n|  zoom            = 7\n| float            = center\n| width            = 300\n| height           = 206\n| caption          =\n|   title          =\n|    minimap       = file\n|  mini-file       = Canada location map.svg\n| mini-width       = 120\n|mini-height       = 64\n|  minipog-x       = 105\n|  minipog-y       = 48\n|  scalemark       = 120 <!-- shifts the scalemark further to the left -->\n|      shape1      = image\n|       mark1      = Red pog.svg\n|      label1      = Portapique\n| mark-coord1      = {{coord|45.3972|-63.7067}}\n|  label-pos1      = bottom\n| label-size1      = 10\n|label-color1      = black\n| label-offset-x1  =\n| label-offset-y1  =\n|mark-title1       = [[Portapique, Nova Scotia]]\n|mark-image1       =\n|mark-description1 =\n\n|      label2      = Wentworth\n|       mark2      = Red pog.svg\n| mark-size2       = 8\n|  label-pos2      = left\n| label-size2      = 10\n|label-color2      = black\n| mark-coord2      = {{coord|45.6564|-63.5493}}\n|mark-title2       = [[Wentworth, Nova Scotia]]\n\n|      label3      = Shubenacadie\n|       mark3      = Red pog.svg\n| mark-size3       = 8\n|  label-pos3      = left\n| label-size3      = 10\n|label-color3      = black\n| mark-coord3      = {{coord|45.0879|-63.4019}}\n|mark-title3       = [[Shubenacadie, Nova Scotia]]\n\n|      label4      = Enfield\n|       mark4      = Red pog.svg\n| mark-size4       = 8\n|  label-pos4      = left\n| label-size4      = 10\n|label-color4      = black\n| mark-coord4      = {{coord|44.9274|-63.5366}}\n|mark-title4       = [[Enfield, Nova Scotia]]\n}}\n| partof           = \n| image            = \n| image_size       = \n| alt              = \n| caption          = \n| map              = \n| map_size         = \n| map_alt          = \n| map_caption      = Portapique in Nova Scotia\n| susperp          = \n| location         = [[Nova Scotia]], Canada\n| target           = \n| date             = {{start date|2020|4|18}}\u2013{{end date|2020|4|19}}\n| time             = \n| timezone         = [[UTC\u221203:00]]\n| coordinates      = \n| type             = [[Spree killer|Spree shooting]], [[mass shooting]],<ref name=\"Vox\" /> [[arson]]\n| weapons          = Firearm(s)\n| fatalities       = At least 19 (including the perpetrator)<ref name=\"CBC3\"/>\n| injuries         = At least 2<ref name=\"CBC3\"/>\n| victim           = \n| perp             = Gabriel Wortman\n| numparts         = \n| numpart          = \n| dfens            = \n| dfen             = \n| footage          = \n| motive           = Under investigation\n}}\n\nOn April 18 and April 19, 2020, Gabriel Wortman killed at least 18 people and set fire to at least five buildings in the [[Canadian province]] of [[Nova Scotia]] before being killed by the [[RCMP]] following a vehicle pursuit.<ref name=\"CBC4\">{{cite news|url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/nova-scotia/mass-killing-shooting-victims-remembered-1.5538032|title=Teacher, family of 3 and RCMP officer among victims of N.S. shooting rampage|publisher=CBC News|accessdate=April 20, 2020|date=April 19, 2020}}</ref>\n\nIt is the deadliest attack involving the use of firearms in Canadian history, surpassing the 1989 [[\u00c9cole Polytechnique massacre]], during which 15 people were killed.<ref name=\"AP\">{{cite news|url=https://apnews.com/7c9a33ae52420e0ddbfb5275898a7e79|title=16 killed in shooting rampage, deadliest in Canadian history|last=Gillies|first=Rob|publisher=Associated Press|accessdate=April 19, 2020|date=April 19, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200419202425/https://apnews.com/7c9a33ae52420e0ddbfb5275898a7e79|archive-date=April 19, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Police say the motive has not yet been established.<ref name=\"nyt-nova-scotia-shooting-gabriel-wortman\">{{Cite news|last=Diaz|first=Johnny|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/04/19/world/canada/nova-scotia-shooting-gabriel-wortman.html|title=Nova Scotia Shooting Kills at Least 16, Police Say|date=April 19, 2020|newspaper=[[The New York Times]]|access-date=April 19, 2020|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200419142013/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/04/19/world/canada/nova-scotia-shooting-gabriel-wortman.html|archive-date=April 19, 2020|last2=Bilefsky|first2=Dan}}</ref><ref name=\"Politico\">{{cite news|last=Blatchford|first=Andy|url=https://www.politico.com/news/2020/04/19/at-least-10-dead-in-canadian-shooting-rampage-195506|title=Gunman kills at least 16, including officer, in Nova Scotia|date=April 19, 2020|accessdate=April 20, 2020|publisher=Politico}}</ref>\n\n==Timeline==\nOn April 18, at around 11:00 p.m. [[Atlantic Time Zone|ADT]], [[Royal Canadian Mounted Police]] (RCMP) officers responded to multiple [[9-1-1]] calls regarding a gun-related incident in the community of [[Portapique]], {{convert|130|km|mi}} north of [[Halifax, Nova Scotia|Halifax]].<ref name=\"CBC3\">{{cite news|url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/nova-scotia/mass-killings-what-we-know-what-we-don-t-1.5537918|title=Nova Scotia mass killings: What we know and what we don't know|date=April 19, 2020|accessdate=April 19, 2020|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200420034520/https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/nova-scotia/mass-killings-what-we-know-what-we-don-t-1.5537918|archive-date=April 20, 2020|publisher=CBC News}}</ref><ref name=\"nyt-nova-scotia-shooting-gabriel-wortman\" /><ref name=\"CBC2\">{{cite news|url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/nova-scotia/nova-scotia-timeline-active-shooter-portapique-1.5537756|title=Timeline: How an active-shooter situation unfolded in Nova Scotia|date=April 19, 2020|accessdate=April 19, 2020|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200420001136/https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/nova-scotia/nova-scotia-timeline-active-shooter-portapique-1.5537756|archive-date=April 20, 2020|publisher=CBC News}}</ref><ref name=\"NBC\">{{cite news|last1=Madani|first1=Doha|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/world/canadian-authorities-say-mass-shooting-suspect-may-have-been-disguised-n1187381|title=16 dead, including officer, in shooting, Canadian authorities say|date=April 19, 2020|accessdate=April 19, 2020|publisher=NBC News|last2=Stelloh|first2=Tim}}</ref> Three houses on Portapique Beach Road were found on fire, and at least five victims were located; they were \"gunned down as they tried to escape the flames.\" One of the first officers to respond to the scene reported by radio that they had yet to locate an armed suspect, and that \"it's very bad what's going on down here.\"<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite news|last=Tasker|first=John Paul|url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/politics/nova-scotia-tick-tock-murder-rampage-1.5539000|title='Those scars will never heal': piecing together a gunman's murderous rampage in Nova Scotia|date=April 20, 2020|work=CBC News|access-date=April 21, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"ABC\">{{cite news|last=Deliso|first=Meredith|url=https://abcnews.go.com/International/multiple-victims-canada-shooting-suspect-dressed-police-officer/story?id=70232582|title=16 dead, including police officer, in deadliest shooting in Canadian history|date=April 19, 2020|accessdate=April 19, 2020|publisher=ABC News}}</ref>\n\nAt 11:32 p.m., the RCMP sent a [[Twitter|tweet]] asking residents of the area to stay inside with their doors locked, but no message was sent through the provincial [[Emergency Alert System|emergency alert system]]. The investigation developed overnight, and by the morning of April 19, police said they were dealing with an [[active shooter]] situation.<ref name=\"CBC3\" /><ref name=\"nyt-nova-scotia-shooting-gabriel-wortman\" /><ref name=\"CBC2\" /><ref name=\"MassLive\">{{cite news|url=https://www.masslive.com/news/2020/04/nova-scotia-shooting-gabriel-wortman-kills-16-including-police-officer-in-canadas-deadliest-shooting-attack.html|title=Nova Scotia shooting: Gabriel Wortman kills 16 including police officer in Canada's deadliest shooting attack|date=April 19, 2020|accessdate=April 19, 2020|publisher=MassLive}}</ref>\n\nAt around 8:00 a.m., a 9-1-1 caller reported \"an explosion and gunfire\" at a house on Hunter Road in [[Wentworth, Nova Scotia|Wentworth]], approximately {{convert|37|km|mi}} north of Portapique. The two residents were killed, as was a neighbour who went to render assistance. Another victim was then shot and killed while walking in the community of [[Wentworth Valley]], on the road back south to Portapique.<ref name=\"CBC4\" />\n\nRCMP identified Wortman, age 51, as the suspect at 8:54 a.m., and warned that he was [[Police impersonation|dressed as an RCMP officer and operating a replica police vehicle]].<ref name=\"CBC2\" /><ref name=\"CTV\">{{cite news|last=Jerrett|first=Andrea|url=https://atlantic.ctvnews.ca/nova-scotia-shooting-suspect-shot-and-killed-by-police-1.4902687|title=At least 18 people killed in N.S. shooting; deadliest such attack in Canada: police|date=April 19, 2020|accessdate=April 19, 2020|publisher=CTV News}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Shah|first=Maryam|url=https://globalnews.ca/news/6840120/nova-scotia-shooting-timeline/|title=Timeline: What we know about the Nova Scotia shooting spree|date=April 19, 2020|accessdate=April 19, 2020|publisher=Global News}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ctvnews.ca/canada/a-timeline-of-the-deadly-shooting-incident-in-nova-scotia-1.4902954|title=A timeline of the deadly shooting incident in Nova Scotia|last1=Neustaeter|first1=Brooklyn|last2=Lopez-Martinez|first2=Melissa|date=April 19, 2020|website=CTV News|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200420053707/https://www.ctvnews.ca/canada/a-timeline-of-the-deadly-shooting-incident-in-nova-scotia-1.4902954|archive-date=April 20, 2020|access-date=April 19, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"CBC\">{{cite news|url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/nova-scotia/rcmp-weapon-lockdown-portapique-1.5537598|title=RCMP officer among the dead after Nova Scotia gunman's rampage|date=April 19, 2020|accessdate=April 19, 2020|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200419130936/https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/nova-scotia/rcmp-weapon-lockdown-portapique-1.5537598|archive-date=April 19, 2020|publisher=CBC News}}</ref> Between 10:04 and 11:04 a.m., he was sighted in or near the communities of [[Glenholme]], [[Debert]], and [[Brookfield, Nova Scotia|Brookfield]], indicating he was travelling south along [[Nova Scotia Highway 102|Highway 102]] toward Halifax.<ref name=\":2\" /> A law enforcement source told [[CNN]] that during this time, Wortman began randomly pulling drivers over and killing them.<ref name=\"CNN\" />\n\nSometime shortly before 11:24 a.m., Wortman encountered RCMP Constable Heidi Stevenson along [[Nova Scotia Trunk 2|Highway 2]], in the community of [[Shubenacadie, Nova Scotia|Shubenacadie]]. Witnesses reported seeing Wortman run towards Stevenson and hearing an exchange of gunfire, which killed Stevenson and injured another officer.<ref name=\"CBC\" /> Two burning cars were observed at the scene, including an RCMP cruiser which may have been Wortman's replica.<ref name=\"CBC6\">{{cite news|url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/nova-scotia/mass-killings-shooting-community-reaction-1.5538181|title=Death toll from Nova Scotia gunman's rampage climbs to 19|date=April 20, 2020|accessdate=April 20, 2020|publisher=CBC News}}</ref> Thereafter, he continued south in a silver [[Chevrolet Tracker (Americas)|Chevrolet Tracker]] [[Sport utility vehicle|SUV]] stolen from one of his victims, and he was next seen in [[Milford (Halifax), Nova Scotia|Milford]].<ref name=\"CBC2\" /><ref name=\"BBC\">{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-52346447|title=Canada shooting: Gunman kills at least 18 in Nova Scotia|date=April 19, 2020|accessdate=April 19, 2020|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200419211041/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-52346447|archive-date=April 19, 2020|publisher=BBC News}}</ref>\n\nFinally, at 11:40 a.m., over 12 hours after police responded to the first firearms complaint, Wortman was shot and killed by police at the [[Irving Oil|Irving]] Big Stop gas station in [[Enfield, Nova Scotia|Enfield]], about {{convert|92|km|mi}} south of Portapique and about {{convert|40|km|mi}} north of Halifax.<ref name=\"Vox\">{{cite news|last=Collins|first=Sean|url=https://www.vox.com/world/2020/4/19/21227349/mass-shooting-nova-scotia-canada-enfield-portapique|title=What we know about a mass shooting in Nova Scotia, Canada|date=April 19, 2020|accessdate=April 19, 2020|publisher=Vox}}</ref><ref name=\"CBC2\" /><ref name=\"CTV\" />\n\n==Investigation==\nNo official motive has been established for the killings, which are not considered an act of [[Terrorism in Canada|terrorism]].<ref name=\"nyt-nova-scotia-shooting-gabriel-wortman\" />\n\nOn the afternoon of April 20, RCMP Chief Superintendent Chris Leather said there were 16 crime scenes in total, including five structure fires, which were scattered over a distance of at least {{convert|50|km|mi}}. He said he expected the death toll to rise as these crime scenes are investigated further.<ref name=\"CBC6\" />\n\nCiting an unnamed law enforcement source, CNN reported that the incident may have begun as a case of domestic violence at one of the homes in Portapique, where Wortman was allegedly trying to find a former partner.<ref name=\"CNN\" />\n\n[[Nova Scotia]]'s [[Serious Incident Response Team]] announced it would conduct an investigation into the officer-involved shooting, as well as a second police use-of-force incident.<ref name=\"CBC\" /><ref name=\"CBC6\" /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://sirt.novascotia.ca/investigation-begins-enfield-death|title=INVESTIGATION BEGINS INTO ENFIELD DEATH|publisher=Serious Incident Response Team|date=April 19, 2020|accessdate=April 20, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://sirt.novascotia.ca/sirt-investigate-discharge-firearm-rcmp-officers|title=SIRT TO INVESTIGATE DISCHARGE OF FIREARM BY RCMP OFFICERS|publisher=Serious Incident Response Team|date=April 20, 2020|accessdate=April 20, 2020}}</ref>\n\nQuestions were raised about why Nova Scotia did not use its [[emergency alert system]] to warn the public about the killings. The RCMP used Twitter to provide updates, but the areas affected had poor Internet service and were mostly populated by seniors who might not use social media. Usage of Nova Scotia's emergency alert system would have sent text messages advising residents of what was happening and to stay indoors. Superintendent Leather said an investigation would be conducted into the decision-making process to alert the public.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/nova-scotia/ns-public-alert-1.5538286|title=N.S. premier not ready to question if a public alert should have been issued about gunman|publisher=CBC News|last=Gorman|first=Michael|date=April 20, 2020|accessdate=April 20, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Victims==\nWortman killed at least 18 people, one of them RCMP Constable Heidi Stevenson, a 23-year veteran. He shot and wounded a second RCMP officer, who is in stable condition.<ref name=\"CBC3\"/><ref name=\"CBC\" /><ref name=\"global-news-rcmp-active-shooter-portapique-n-s\">{{Cite news|last=Quon|first=Alexander|url=https://globalnews.ca/news/6838880/rcmp-active-shooter-portapique-n-s/|title=17 dead, including one RCMP officer, after shooting spree in Portapique, N.S.|date=April 19, 2020|access-date=April 19, 2020|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200419202613/https://globalnews.ca/news/6838880/rcmp-active-shooter-portapique-n-s/|archive-date=April 19, 2020|publisher=[[Global News]]|last2=Stephenson|first2=Mercedes}}</ref> At least one other person was injured.<ref name=\"CBC3\" /> According to Commissioner [[Brenda Lucki]], some of his first victims were closely connected to him, but as he continued, his targets became more random.<ref name=\"nyt-nova-scotia-shooting-gabriel-wortman\" /> The dead are believed to have died from gunshot wounds, but other causes are also being investigated.<ref name=\"CBC3\" /><ref name=\"BBC\" /> The RCMP expects to find more bodies within the remnants of five structure fires.<ref name=\"CTV4\">{{cite web|url=https://www.ctvnews.ca/canada/nova-scotia-rampage-results-in-18-victims-16-crime-scenes-1.4903398|title=Nova Scotia rampage results in 18 victims, 16 crime scenes|date=April 20, 2020|work=[[CTV News]]|first=Meredith|last=MacLeod|accessdate=April 20, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Perpetrator==\nThe RCMP identified the perpetrator as Gabriel Wortman, a [[denturist]] working in the Halifax area. He owned real estate in Portapique and [[Dartmouth, Nova Scotia|Dartmouth]].<ref name=\"CBC\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/apr/20/nova-scotia-shooting-gunman-profile-quiet-gentle-denturist|title=Nova Scotia shooting: shock and surprise at killings by denturist|first=Leyland|last=Cecco|date=April 19, 2020|accessdate=April 19, 2020|website=The Guardian}}</ref> He attended [[Riverview High School (New Brunswick)|Riverview High School]] in New Brunswick and aspired to be a police officer.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://atlantic.ctvnews.ca/just-unbelievable-neighbours-of-nova-scotia-shooting-suspect-shocked-by-news-1.4903021|title='Just unbelievable': Neighbours of Nova Scotia shooting suspect shocked by news|date=April 19, 2020|website=CTV News|language=en|access-date=April 20, 2020}}</ref> Acquaintances described him as a house-proud and polite man who often spent time at a seasonal home near [[Cobequid Bay]].<ref name=\"CTV5\">{{cite news|url=https://www.ctvnews.ca/canada/what-we-know-about-the-nova-scotia-rampage-suspect-1.4903920|title=What we know about the Nova Scotia rampage suspect|publisher=CTV News|last=Bogart|first=Nicole|date=April 20, 2020|accessdate=April 20, 2020}}</ref>\n\nWortman had a hobby of buying law enforcement memorabilia and refurbishing old police cruisers. One person called his home a \"shrine\" for the RCMP.<ref name=\":0\">{{cite news|url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/canada/article-nova-scotia-mass-shooter-was-a-denturist-with-an-obsession-for/|title=Nova Scotia mass shooter was a denturist with an obsession for policing|publisher=The Globe and Mail|last1=Woo|first1=Andrew|last2=Mercer|first2=Greg|date=April 19, 2020|accessdate=April 20, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200420055810/https://www.theglobeandmail.com/canada/article-nova-scotia-mass-shooter-was-a-denturist-with-an-obsession-for/|archive-date=April 20, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> He stored the two old police cruisers that he bought behind his dental clinic.<ref name=\":1\" /><ref name=\"CTV5\" />\n\nNeighbours said Wortman struggled with [[alcohol use]] and his profitable business was impacted by the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Nova Scotia|coronavirus pandemic]], which forced all non-essential dental services to cease.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n==Reactions==\nFlags across Canada were lowered to [[half-mast]],<ref name=\"Guardian2\">{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/apr/20/nova-scotia-shooting-friends-family-pay-tribute-victims|title=Nova Scotia shooting: friends and family pay tribute to 'beautiful souls' lost in rampage|publisher=The Guardian|last=Cecco|first=Leyland|date=April 20, 2020|accessdate=April 20, 2020}}</ref> and the [[House of Commons of Canada|House of Commons]] observed a moment of silence for the victims.<ref>{{cite web| url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/politics/trudeau-nova-scotia-shooting-1.5538301| title='We're going to get through this together': Trudeau calls for unity after mass killing| website=CBC News| date=April 20, 2020| accessdate=April 20, 2020| url-status=live| archive-url=http://archive.is/7qFSQ| archive-date=April 20, 2020}}</ref>\n\n[[Nova Scotia Premier]] [[Stephen McNeil]] told reporters, \"This is one of the most senseless acts of violence in our province's history.\" He expressed his condolences to the residents affected and the families of the victims.<ref name=\"CTV2\">{{cite news|url=https://atlantic.ctvnews.ca/shooting-one-of-the-most-senseless-acts-of-violence-in-nova-scotia-s-history-premier-1.4902917|title=Shooting 'one of the most senseless acts of violence' in Nova Scotia's history: premier|last=Jerrett|first=Andrea|publisher=CTV News|accessdate=April 19, 2020|date=April 19, 2020}}</ref> \n\nCanadian Prime Minister [[Justin Trudeau]] also expressed his condolences.<ref name=\"CBC\" /> During his morning address from [[Rideau Cottage]] on April 20, he reaffirmed his commitment to strengthening gun control.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ctvnews.ca/politics/trudeau-reiterates-gun-control-commitment-in-wake-of-mass-shooting-1.4903966|title=Trudeau reiterates gun control commitment in wake of mass shooting|publisher=CTV News|last=Gilmore|first=Rachel|date=April 20, 2020|accessdate=April 20, 2020}}</ref> Trudeau also asked the media to avoid so much as mentioning Wortman's name or publishing a photograph of him. \"Do not give this person the gift of infamy\", Trudeau said.<ref name=name>{{cite news|url=https://www.macleans.ca/opinion/the-killers-name/|author=Terry Glavin|title=The killer's name|publisher=''Maclean's''|date=20 April 2020|accessdate=21 April 2020]</ref> \n\nThe [[White House]] condemned the killings and expressed US President [[Donald Trump]] and First Lady [[Melania Trump]]'s condolences.<ref name=\"CNN\">{{cite news|url=https://www.cnn.com/2020/04/20/americas/nova-scotia-shooting-monday/index.html|title=Gunman evaded police for nearly 12 hours and killed at least 18 in one of Canada's deadliest mass shootings|publisher=CNN|last1=McLaughlin|first1=Eliott C.|last2=Newton|first2=Paula|date=April 20, 2020|accessdate=April 20, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[Moncton shooting]]\n* [[List of massacres in Canada]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:2020 crimes in Canada]]\n[[Category:2020 in Nova Scotia]]\n[[Category:2020 mass shootings]]\n[[Category:2020 mass shootings in North America]]\n[[Category:2020 murders in North America]]\n[[Category:2020s mass shootings in North America]]\n[[Category:21st-century mass murder in North America]]\n[[Category:April 2020 crimes]]\n[[Category:April 2020 events in Canada]]\n[[Category:Arson in Canada]]\n[[Category:Arson in the 2020s]]\n[[Category:Attacks on buildings and structures in 2020]]\n[[Category:Crime in Nova Scotia]]\n[[Category:Death in Nova Scotia]]\n[[Category:Deaths by firearm in Canada]]\n[[Category:Mass shootings in Canada]]\n[[Category:Mass murder in Canada]]\n[[Category:Royal Canadian Mounted Police]]\n[[Category:Spree shootings in Canada]]\n", "name_user": "InedibleHulk", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eInvestigation:Singular.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nova_Scotia_killings"}
{"title_page": "My Youth Romantic Comedy Is Wrong, As I Expected", "text_new": "{{Infobox animanga/Header\n| name            = My Youth Romantic Comedy Is Wrong, As I Expected\n| image           = My Teen Romantic Comedy SNAFU cover.jpg\n| caption         = Cover of the first light novel volume, featuring Hachiman Hikigaya and Yukino Yukinoshita\n| ja_kanji        = \u3084\u306f\u308a\u4ffa\u306e\u9752\u6625\u30e9\u30d6\u30b3\u30e1\u306f\u307e\u3061\u304c\u3063\u3066\u3044\u308b\u3002\n| ja_romaji       = Yahari Ore no Seishun Rabukome wa Machigatteiru.\n| genre           = [[Romance novel|Romance]], [[comedy]], [[slice of life]]<ref name=\"Official Sentai\"/><!-- Genres should be based on what reliable sources list them as and not on personal interpretations. Limit of the three most relevant genres in accordance with [[MOS:A&M]]. -->\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Print\n| type            = light novel\n| author          = Wataru Watari\n| illustrator     = Ponkan8\n| publisher       = [[Shogakukan]]\n| publisher_en    = {{English manga publisher|NA =[[Yen Press]]}}\n| demographic     = Male\n| imprint         = [[Gagaga Bunko]]\n| first           = March 18, 2011\n| last            = November 19, 2019\n| volumes         = 14 + 3 short story collections\n| volume_list     = #Light novels\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Print\n| type            = manga\n| title           = My Youth Romantic Comedy Is Wrong, As I Expected -Monologue-\n| author          = Rechi Kazuki\n| publisher       = [[Square Enix]]\n| demographic     = ''[[Seinen manga|Seinen]]''\n| magazine        = Big Gangan\n| first           = September 25, 2012\n| last            = \n| volumes         = 16\n| volume_list     = #My Youth Romantic Comedy Is Wrong, As I Expected -Monologue- volumes\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Print\n| type            = manga\n| title           = My Youth Romantic Comedy Is Wrong, As I Expected @ comic\n| author          = Naomichi Io\n| publisher       = Shogakukan\n| publisher_en    = {{English manga publisher|NA =[[Yen Press]]}}\n| demographic     = ''Seinen''\n| magazine        = [[Monthly Sunday Gene-X]]\n| first           = December 19, 2012\n| last            = \n| volumes         = 15\n| volume_list     = #My Youth Romantic Comedy Is Wrong, As I Expected @comic volumes\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Print\n| type            = manga\n| title           = Yahari 4-koma demo Ore no Seishun Rabu Kome wa machigatteiru.\n| author          = Y\u016bta Taneda\n| publisher       = [[Ichijinsha]]\n| demographic     = ''Seinen''\n| magazine        = Manga 4-koma Palette\n| first           = April 22, 2013\n| last            = June 22, 2015\n| volumes         = 2\n| volume_list     = \n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Video\n| title           = My Teen Romantic Comedy SNAFU\n| type            = TV series\n| director        = Ai Yoshimura\n| writer          = Sh\u014dtar\u014d Suga\n| music           = Kakeru Ishihama <small>(Monaca)</small>\n| studio          = [[Brain's Base]]\n| licensee        = {{English anime licensee\n | AUS = [[Madman Entertainment]]\n | NA  = [[Sentai Filmworks]]\n | UK=[[Animatsu Entertainment]]\n}}\n| network         = [[Tokyo Broadcasting System|TBS]], [[Mainichi Broadcasting System|MBS]], [[Chubu-Nippon Broadcasting|CBC]], [[BS-TBS]]\n| network_en      = {{English anime network\n |NA=[[Anime Network]]\n |SEA=[[Animax Asia]]\n}}\n| first           = April 5, 2013\n| last            = June 28, 2013\n| episodes        = 13 + OVA\n| episode_list    = My Teen Romantic Comedy SNAFU (season 1)\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Game\n| title           = Yahari Game demo Ore no Seishun Rabukome wa Machigatteiru.\n| developer       = [[5pb.]]\n| publisher       = 5pb.\n| genre           = \n| platforms       = [[PlayStation Vita]]\n| released        = {{vgrelease|JP|September 19, 2013}}\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Video\n| title           = My Teen Romantic Comedy SNAFU TOO!\n| type            = TV series\n| director        = Kei Oikawa\n| writer          = Sh\u014dtar\u014d Suga\n| music           = Kakeru Ishihama <small>(Monaca)</small><br/>Kuniyuki Takahashi <small>(Monaca)</small>\n| studio          = [[Feel (animation studio)|Feel]]\n| licensee        = {{English anime licensee\n | AUS = Madman Entertainment\n | NA  = Sentai Filmworks\n | UK=Animatsu Entertainment\n}}\n| network         = TBS, CBC, [[Tulip Television|TUT]], MBS, BS-TBS\n| network_en      = {{English anime network\n  |NA=[[Anime Network]]\n}}\n| first           = April 3, 2015\n| last            = June 26, 2015\n| episodes        = 13 + OVA\n| episode_list    = My Teen Romantic Comedy SNAFU (season 2)\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Game\n| title           = Yahari Game demo Ore no Seishun Rabukome wa Machigatteiru. Zoku\n| developer       = [[5pb.]]\n| publisher       = 5pb.\n| genre           = \n| platforms       = [[PlayStation Vita]]\n| released        = {{vgrelease|JP|October 27, 2016}}\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Video\n| title           = My Teen Romantic Comedy SNAFU Climax\n| type            = TV series\n| director        = Kei Oikawa\n| writer          = Keiichir\u014d \u014cchi\n| music           = Kakeru Ishihama <small>(Monaca)</small><br/>Kuniyuki Takahashi <small>(Monaca)</small>\n| studio          = Feel\n| licensee        = Sentai Filmworks <!-- Worldwide excluding Asia -->\n| network         = TBS, MBS, CBC,  BS-TBS\n| first           = \n| last            = \n| episodes        = \n| episode_list    = \n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Footer}}\n\n{{Nihongo|'''''My Youth Romantic Comedy Is Wrong, As I Expected'''''|\u3084\u306f\u308a\u4ffa\u306e\u9752\u6625\u30e9\u30d6\u30b3\u30e1\u306f\u307e\u3061\u304c\u3063\u3066\u3044\u308b\u3002|Yahari Ore no Seishun Rabukome wa Machigatteiru.|lead=yes}}, abbreviated as {{nihongo|'''''OreGairu'''''|\u4ffa\u30ac\u30a4\u30eb}} and {{nihongo|'''''Hamachi'''''|\u306f\u307e\u3061}},<ref>{{cite web|url=http://d.hatena.ne.jp/watariwataru/20110215/1297794528|script-title=ja:\u300e\u3084\u306f\u308a\u4ffa\u306e\u9752\u6625\u30e9\u30d6\u30b3\u30e1\u306f\u307e\u3061\u304c\u3063\u3066\u3044\u308b\u3002\u300f\u7565\u79f0\u3092\u8003\u3048\u308b\u30b3\u30fc\u30ca\u30fc|language=Japanese|publisher=Wataru Watari|date=2011-02-15|accessdate=2013-01-10|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6FhCQlmRa?url=http://d.hatena.ne.jp/watariwataru/20110215/1297794528|archivedate=2013-04-07}}</ref> and also known as '''''My Teen Romantic Comedy SNAFU''''', is a Japanese [[light novel]] series written by Wataru Watari and illustrated by Ponkan8. The series follows Hachiman Hikigaya, a pessimistic, closeminded, and realistic teen, who is forced by his teacher to join the school's service club and work with two girls with issues of their own. They offer help and advice to others while dealing with their inner conflicts.\n\nThere are three manga adaptations and two [[anthology]] volumes. It has been adapted into an [[anime]] television series, which aired between April 4 and June 27, 2013 and was followed by a second season which aired between April 2 and June 25, 2015, as well as an upcoming third and final season. ''Yahari Game demo Ore no Seishun Rabukome wa Machigatteiru'', a video game was released by [[5pb.]], for the [[PlayStation Vita]] was released on September 19, 2013. A second video game also by 5pb was released on October 27, 2016.\n\n==Characters==\n===Main characters===\nThe main characters in the series are members of the school's service club, which is run by Yukino Yukinoshita.\n\n;{{Nihongo|Hachiman Hikigaya|\u6bd4\u4f01\u8c37 \u516b\u5e61|Hikigaya Hachiman}}{{anchor|Hachiman Hikigaya}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Takuya Eguchi]]|[[Adam Gibbs]]<ref name=\"Dub cast\">{{cite web|url=https://www.sentaifilmworks.com/a/news/my-romantic-comedy-snafu-official-english-cast-list|title=My Romantic Comedy SNAFU Official English Cast List|work=[[Sentai Filmworks]]|date=September 16, 2019|accessdate=September 16, 2019}}</ref>}}\n: The [[viewpoint character]] of the light novels, Hachiman is a student in class 2F of S\u014dbu High School who has been discriminated in the past to the point that he becomes isolated, friendless, and pragmatic to a fault. His most prominent feature is his set of \"dead fish-eyes\" that puts people off. Due to years of social isolation, he has developed a habit of observing people in his surroundings from a distance, earning him a skill for social perception, figuring out the true nature of people. He believes that youth is an illusion created by hypocrites, for hypocrites, born from his past failures. His experience leads him to believe the happiness of others is a facade. He is affectionately called \"Hikki\" by Yui. Hayato's clique wrongly address him as \"Hikitani\".\n\n: His teacher Shizuka worries about him becoming a social outcast and forces him to join the Service Club. Hachiman believes himself to be an insignificant entity and is willing to take the blame in order to keep everyone else happy.\n: On the first day of high school, he winds up in a car accident from trying to save Yui's puppy and ends up in the hospital for three weeks, making him an outsider once he gets back because the whole class has already formed its cliques. He thinks that Yui's feelings for him are due to guilt and thus, indirectly rejects Yui, thinking he would cause trouble for her. He also distances himself from Yukino after realizing that the car that rammed into him belongs to her family. In both cases, they make amends with him once said misunderstandings are cleared. It is suggested that he is aware of the girl's feelings, due to studying people's behavior and doesn't accept them as genuine.\n;{{Nihongo|Yukino Yukinoshita|\u96ea\u30ce\u4e0b \u96ea\u4e43|Yukinoshita Yukino}}{{anchor|Yukino Yukinoshita}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Saori Hayami]]|Melissa Molano<ref name=\"Dub cast\" />}}\n: Yukino is a student in class 2J and the leader of the Service Club but was the sole member until Hachiman joined. Born to a wealthy family, she is smart, beautiful, and nicknamed the \"Ice-cold Beauty\" for her icy demeanour. She shows no empathy and little kindness towards Hachiman at first, but eventually opens up to him. Due to her talent and beauty, she is envied by most girls and is disgusted by their attitude to undermine her instead of improving themselves, thus she has few friends. She has a twisted sense of ''noblesse oblige'', and believes it is the duty of the exceptional to help the \"lost lambs\" of the world. She essentially wants to help others, but is brutally honest and directly analyses their flaws. Her personality often leads her to be disgusted at the naivet\u00e9 and lack of understanding how things work of others, particularly Yui's, and she does not hesitate to show it. Despite this, Yui still affectionately refers to her as \"Yukinon\"; thanks to her, Yukino becomes kinder and the two girls become best friends. She recognizes Hachiman from the car accident but lies about it when Hachiman joins the Service Club. She is devastated when he distances himself from her, after learning it from her sister. Throughout the series, she develops feelings for him.\n;{{nihongo|Yui Yuigahama|\u7531\u6bd4\u30f6\u6d5c \u7d50\u8863|Yuigahama Yui}}{{anchor|Yui Yuigahama}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Nao T\u014dyama]]|Cat Thomas<ref name=\"Dub cast\" />}}\n: Yui is Hachiman's classmate. A cheerful, outgoing girl, she becomes the Service Club's first \"customer,\" asking them to help her bake cookies for \"a certain someone.\" By no means cynical and the friendliest member of the group, her problems lie not with her personality, but with her inability to express herself due to fear of losing friends, and thus admires Yukino and Hachiman, who are able to express their true feelings. She believes that talent is inborn, and often aspires to be like others until Yukino changes her way of thinking. Following her experience with the Service Club, Yui begins to attend Service Club sessions after school as well, despite Yukino's objections early on. In class, Yui is a member of Hayato's clique but has no say in matters as she is often overwhelmed by Yumiko. She has been holding feelings towards Hachiman ever since he saved her dog on the first day of high school.\n\n===Class 2F===\n;{{Nihongo|Saika Totsuka|\u6238\u585a \u5f69\u52a0|Totsuka Saika}}{{anchor|Saika Totsuka}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Mikako Komatsu]]|[[Margaret McDonald (voice actress)|Margaret McDonald]]<ref name=\"Dub cast\" />}}\n: Saika is the president of the tennis club who has an [[androgyny|androgynous appearance]] but prefers others to not mistake his gender. He is called \"The Prince\" by his female classmates. On their first meeting, Saika asks help from Hachiman to join the tennis club, which was brushed off by Yukino. Saika then asked the Service Club to help him improve his tennis skills. He eventually became one of the few people in class 2F who would talk to Hachiman on a first name basis, and often hangs out with him. Despite knowing that Saika is a boy, Hachiman oftentimes finds himself unwillingly attracted to him.\n;{{Nihongo|Hayato Hayama|\u8449\u5c71 \u96bc\u4eba|Hayama Hayato}}{{anchor|Hayato Hayama}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Takashi Kond\u014d]]|Scott Gibbs<ref name=\"Dub cast\" />}}\n: Hayato is Yukino's childhood friend who is a central figure in class 2F and the ace of the football club. He is extremely kind to other people, including Hachiman, and often offers his help to others. However, Hayama claims that he can never forge a good relationship with Hachiman since, despite understanding his acts of social suicide to protect everyone, he does not agree with him. He and Yukino have some strain to their relationship, stemming from an incident in the past, and thus far, his attempts to mend his relationship with Yukino have failed. Despite his popularity and success, he feels largely inferior to Hachiman.\n;{{Nihongo|Yumiko Miura|\u4e09\u6d66 \u512a\u7f8e\u5b50|Miura Yumiko}}{{anchor|Yumiko Miura}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Marina Inoue]]|[[Christina Kelly]]<ref name=\"Dub cast\" />}}\n: Yumiko is a popular girl from class 2F with a pompous personality. She is the main female figure in Hayato's clique and it is hinted that she has feelings for Hayato. Due to her popularity, she has no trouble making friends, and thus has little to no understanding towards people who have social troubles. \n;{{Nihongo|Hina Ebina|\u6d77\u8001\u540d \u59eb\u83dc|Ebina Hina}}{{anchor|Hina Ebina}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Nozomi Sasaki (voice actress)|Nozomi Sasaki]]|Natalie Rial<ref name=\"Dub cast\" />}}.\n:A close friend of Yumiko and Yui's, and a member of Hayato's clique. A massive Yaoi fangirl who loves to see two boys hitting on each other. When she gets riled up, all respect for personal space of others goes out the window. She has an eye for detail, especially for clothing.\n;{{Nihongo|Saki Kawasaki|\u5ddd\u5d0e \u6c99\u5e0c|Kawasaki Saki}}{{anchor|Saki Kawasaki}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Ami Koshimizu]]|Teresa Zimmermann<ref name=\"Dub cast\" />}}\n: Saki is Hachiman's classmate who seems like a delinquent but wants to make friends deep down. She cares deeply for her brother as she hid her name and age to work as a night-shift bartender in order to pay school fees and reduce her family's load. After her brother asked for the Service Club's help, they eventually followed Saki to her workplace and found out her motives behind working night-shifts; she stopped working after the Service Club suggested her to aim for a scholarship instead.\n;{{Nihongo|Kakeru Tobe|\u6238\u90e8 \u7fd4|Tobe Kakeru}}{{anchor|Kakeru Tobe}}\n:{{voiced by|Chado Horii|Gareth West<ref name=\"Dub cast\" />}}\n: Tobe is a member of Hayato's clique who is in the football club. He has feelings for Hina and is the only guy in the class who supported Hina's script for the cultural festival. During the school excursion, he intended to confess to Hina and therefore requested help from the Service Club. However, Hachiman knew Hina did not want to get into a relationship, so he confesses to (and is rejected by) Hina to prevent Tobe from being rejected, thus maintaining the status quo within that group. \n;{{Nihongo|Yamato|\u5927\u548c|Yamato}}{{anchor|Yamato}}\n:{{voiced by|Yoshihisa Kawahara|Orlanders Jones<ref name=\"Dub cast\" />}}\n: Yamato is a member of Hayato's clique who is in the rugby club.\n;{{Nihongo|\u014coka|\u5927\u5ca1|\u014coka}}{{anchor|\u014coka}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Minoru Shiraishi]]|Daniel Regojo<ref name=\"Dub cast\" />}}\n: \u014coka is a member of Hayato's clique who is in the baseball club.\n;{{Nihongo|Minami Sagami|\u76f8\u6a21 \u5357|Sagami Minami}}{{anchor|Minami Sagami}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Minako Kotobuki]]|[[Caitlynn French]]<ref name=\"Dub cast\" />}}\n: Minami is the leader of the second most influential clique in class 2F and holds a grudge towards Yui, who she was friendly with during their first high school year, for being in the superior clique. She volunteered to be event organizer for the cultural festival in order to promote her worth without the actual ability to do such a job, and thus requested help from the Service Club. As such, Yukino took up the role of an assistant event organizer and claimed the spotlight in making the cultural festival a successful one, which in turn made Minami depressed about her own uselessness and refused to host the closing ceremony. However, as Hachiman's fierce scolding has successfully turned himself into the scapegoat and shifted the blame away from Minami, she attended the closing ceremony and ended the cultural festival on a high note.\n\n===Others===\n;{{Nihongo|Shizuka Hiratsuka|\u5e73\u585a \u9759|Hiratsuka Shizuka}}{{anchor|Shizuka Hiratsuka}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Ryoka Yuzuki]]|Heidi Hinkel<ref name=\"Dub cast\" />}}\n: Shizuka is Hachiman's teacher, a language teacher who serves as his futures advisor/ counsellor and the consultant for the service club. She is aware of Hachiman's supposed \"problems\", and takes steps to ensure he is freed from them, her first move being to force him into joining the Service Club. However, she appears to have some quirks of her own: she is a young smoker, she is very sensitive about her age and single status, and she is often prone to quoting or copying scenes from popular [[sh\u014dnen manga]]. Additionally, she never remembers to knock before entering the Service Club's classroom, much to Yukino's chagrin. After the cultural festival incident, she tells Hachiman that helping others should not be a reason for Hachiman to hurt himself, as there are others who would feel pain seeing Hachiman hurt.\n;{{Nihongo|Komachi Hikigaya|\u6bd4\u4f01\u8c37 \u5c0f\u753a|Hikigaya Komachi}}{{anchor|Komachi Hikigaya}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Aoi Y\u016bki]]|[[Hilary Haag]]<ref name=\"Dub cast\" />}}\n: Komachi is Hachiman's younger sister who, different from her brother, is cheerful and lively, and is a member of the student council in her school. She understands her brother's anti-social personality, cares for, and relies on him. While attached to her brother, she shows cleverness in trying to pair up Hachiman with Yukino or Yui.\n;{{Nihongo|Yoshiteru Zaimokuza|\u6750\u6728\u5ea7 \u7fa9\u8f1d|Zaimokuza Yoshiteru}}{{anchor|Yoshiteru Zaimokuza}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Nobuyuki Hiyama]]|Andrew Love<ref name=\"Dub cast\" />}}\n: Yoshiteru is a student from class 2C who suffers from adolescent delusions. He sees Hachiman as a friend after being paired up with him during physical education lessons. While he is annoying, he has a group of [[otaku]] friends he's on good terms with. He aims to be a light novel writer.\n;{{Nihongo|Haruno Yukinoshita|\u96ea\u30ce\u4e0b \u967d\u4e43|Yukinoshita Haruno}}{{anchor|Haruno Yukinoshita}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Mai Nakahara]]|Olivia Swasey<ref name=\"Dub cast\" />}}\n: Haruno is Yukino's elder sister. Unlike Yukino, she shows a good attitude towards other people at first but eventually shows a sinister personality. Despite being a college student she spends a good deal of time spying on her sister's life. Yukino holds strong animosity towards her and Haruno can only say her sister constantly tries to overtake her as cute. Nonetheless, Haruno eventually shows her own grudges against Yukino and makes Yukino and Hachiman feel bad in the 2nd season.\n: She is a former student of S\u014dbu High School. She acknowledges Hachiman's perceptiveness and often playfully teases him.\n: Her being beautiful, rich, and charismatic makes people (including the series' audience) only see her good side, defer to her and ignore big problems she causes to others. For instance, in the 1st season, Haruno appears suddenly to abruptly intervene with the Cultural Festival where her role becomes to encourage the President to take it easy, resulting in delayed tasks. Hachiman takes part in picking up the slack and assumes his usual blame-taking role by complaining for the sake of others, complaints that only get him criticized, leading him to a dramatic confrontation with the Festival President.\n;{{Nihongo|Taishi Kawasaki|\u5ddd\u5d0e \u5927\u5fd7|Kawasaki Taishi}}{{anchor|Taishi Kawasaki}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Ayumu Murase]]|Morgan Berry<ref name=\"Dub cast\" />}}\n: Taishi is Saki's little brother and Komachi's classmate. He is on good terms with Komachi and is worried about Saki coming home late every night.\n;{{Nihongo|Rumi Tsurumi|\u9db4\u898b \u7559\u7f8e|Tsurumi Rumi}}{{anchor|Rumi Tsurumi}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Sumire Morohoshi]]|Savanna Menzel<ref name=\"Dub cast\" />}}\n: Rumi is a lonely primary school student who is openly despised by her peers. Hayato at first tried to resolve the situation through talking to her in front of her classmates, which instead attracted more hateful attention to her. Hachiman and company decided that the only way out is to destroy the trust between her peers, through having Hayato and Kakeru acting as bullies threatening Rumi's group-mates during treasure hunt. However, Rumi was able to use her camera's flash as a distraction, allowing the group to escape. \n;{{Nihongo|Meguri Shiromeguri|\u57ce\u5efb \u3081\u3050\u308a|Shiromeguri Meguri}}{{anchor|Meguri Shiromeguri}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Azumi Asakura]]|[[Jad Saxton]]<ref name=\"Dub cast\" />}}\n: Meguri is a third-year student and the former president of S\u014dbu High School's student council. Although she is not a reliable leader herself, her personality has brought her immense support from the councillors and thus she is able to unite the student council.\n;{{Nihongo|Iroha Isshiki|\u4e00\u8272 \u3044\u308d\u306f|Isshiki Iroha}}{{anchor|Iroha Isshiki}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Ayane Sakura]]|[[Luci Christian]]<ref name=\"Dub 2 cast\">{{cite web|url=https://www.sentaifilmworks.com/a/news/my-romantic-comedy-snafu-too-official-english-cast-list|title=My Romantic Comedy SNAFU TOO! Official English Cast List|work=[[Sentai Filmworks]]|date=September 16, 2019|accessdate=September 16, 2019}}</ref>}}\n: Iroha is a first-year student who manages the football team, is cheerful and pretty. As she was recommended as a candidate for the student council president in a prank, out of her dislike of the role, she filed a request to the Service Club in order to not get elected and yet not lose in an embarrassing fashion. She eventually accepts her role of being the student council president after Hachiman managed to convince her. There is a running joke where Iroha mistakes something that Hachiman says or does as flirting, and promptly rejects him.\n;{{Nihongo|Kaori Orimoto|\u6298\u672c \u304b\u304a\u308a|Orimoto Kaori}}{{anchor|Kaori Orimoto}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Haruka Tomatsu]]|[[Kira Vincent-Davis]]<ref name=\"Dub 2 cast\" />}}\n: Kaori is Hachiman's classmate in middle school, whom he confessed to in the past. She attends Kaihin General High School.\n;{{Nihongo|Chika Nakamachi|\u4ef2\u753a \u5343\u4f73|Nakamachi Chika}}{{anchor|Chika Nakamachi}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Saki Fujita]]|Christie Guidry<ref name=\"Dub 2 cast\" />}}\n:Chika is Kaori's friend and schoolmate at Kaihin General. She is interested in Hayato.\n;{{Nihongo|Tamanawa|\u7389\u7e04|}}{{anchor|Tamanawa}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Satoshi Hino]]|Mike Haimoto<ref name=\"Dub 2 cast\" />}}\n:Tamanawa is Kaihin High School's student council president.\n; Mrs. Yukinoshita\n:{{voiced by|[[Kikuko Inoue]]|[[Shelley Calene-Black]]<ref name=\"Dub 2 cast\" />}}\n: She is Haruno and Yukino's mother. She worries for Yukino's whereabouts living alone and has Haruno spy on her. She is disappointed when she runs into Yukino late at night after a student council event.\n; Mrs. Yuigahama\n:{{voiced by|[[Sayaka Ohara]]|[[Monica Rial]]<ref name=\"Dub 2 cast\" />}}\n: She is Yui's mother and has a close mother-daughter relationship with Yui, one which Yukino is envious of.\n\n==Media==\n\n===Light novels===\nThe light novel series is written by Wataru Watari and illustrated by Ponkan8. It is being published by ''[[Shogakukan]]'' under the ''[[Gagaga Bunko]]'' imprint. The first volume was published on March 18, 2011<ref name=\"ln1\" /> and the series was concluded with its 14th volume released on November 19, 2019.<ref name=ln14 />\n\nVolumes 3, 4, 7, and 8 were published simultaneously with limited special editions. The special editions of the 3rd and 7th volumes were bundled with drama CDs<ref name=\"ln3_le\" /><ref name=\"ln7_le\" /> and those of the 4th and 8th volumes \u2013 with art books by Ponkan8 and guest illustrators.<ref name=\"ln4_le\" /><ref name=\"ln8_le\" /> A set of the first 7 volumes was released on March 19, 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.co.jp/dp/B00BOH6TN0|script-title=ja:\u3084\u306f\u308a\u4ffa\u306e\u9752\u6625\u30e9\u30d6\u30b3\u30e1\u306f\u307e\u3061\u304c\u3063\u3066\u3044\u308b\u3002 \u6587\u5eab 1-7\u5dfb\u30bb\u30c3\u30c8 (\u30ac\u30ac\u30ac\u6587\u5eab)|language=Japanese|publisher=[[Amazon.co.jp]]|accessdate=2013-06-09}}</ref> A collection of short stories, volume 7.5, was published on August 20, 2013.<ref name=ln7.5 /> Three additional short volumes, 6.25, 6.50 and 6.75 were bundled with the limited editions of the 1st, 3rd and 5th DVD and BD volumes respectively of the first anime series,<ref name=bd1>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.co.jp/dp/B00CA0C4YS|title=\u3084\u306f\u308a\u4ffa\u306e\u9752\u6625\u30e9\u30d6\u30b3\u30e1\u306f\u307e\u3061\u304c\u3063\u3066\u3044\u308b\u3002\u7b2c1\u5dfb (\u521d\u56de\u9650\u5b9a\u7248)(\u6e21 \u822a\u66f8\u304d\u4e0b\u308d\u3057\u6587\u5eab\u5c0f\u8aac152P\u30fb\u30b5\u30f3\u30c8\u30e9CD\u540c\u68b1) [Blu-ray] (2013)|language=Japanese|publisher=[[Amazon.co.jp]]|accessdate=2013-08-20}}</ref><ref name=bd3>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.co.jp/dp/B00CBDFTW8|title=\u3084\u306f\u308a\u4ffa\u306e\u9752\u6625\u30e9\u30d6\u30b3\u30e1\u306f\u307e\u3061\u304c\u3063\u3066\u3044\u308b\u3002\u7b2c3\u5dfb (\u521d\u56de\u9650\u5b9a\u7248) [Blu-ray]|language=Japanese|publisher=[[Amazon.co.jp]]|accessdate=2013-08-20}}</ref><ref name=bd5>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.co.jp/dp/B00CBDFUW2|title=\u3084\u306f\u308a\u4ffa\u306e\u9752\u6625\u30e9\u30d6\u30b3\u30e1\u306f\u307e\u3061\u304c\u3063\u3066\u3044\u308b\u3002\u7b2c5\u5dfb (\u521d\u56de\u9650\u5b9a\u7248) [Blu-ray]|language=Japanese|publisher=[[Amazon.co.jp]]|accessdate=2013-08-20}}</ref> and were released as single volume, numbered 6.5, on July 22, 2014.<ref name=ln6.5_re /> A limited special edition of it was bundled with a drama CD.<ref name=ln6.5_le /> Another short story collection volume, labeled 10.5, was released on March 18, 2015.<ref name=ln10.5 />\n\n{{Graphic novel list/header\n | Language        = Japanese\n | SecondLanguage  = English\n | LineColor       = CCF\n}}\n{{Graphic novel list\n| VolumeNumber = 1\n| OriginalRelDate = March 18, 2011<ref name=\"ln1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.co.jp/dp/4094512624|script-title=ja:\u3084\u306f\u308a\u4ffa\u306e\u9752\u6625\u30e9\u30d6\u30b3\u30e1\u306f\u307e\u3061\u304c\u3063\u3066\u3044\u308b\u3002 (\u30ac\u30ac\u30ac\u6587\u5eab)|language=Japanese|publisher=[[Amazon.co.jp]]|accessdate=2013-06-09}}</ref>\n| OriginalISBN = 9