ary         = \n}}\n{{Graphic novel list\n | VolumeNumber    = 10\n | OriginalRelDate = November 17, 2017\n | OriginalISBN    = 978-4091575067\n | LicensedRelDate = March 19, 2019\n | LicensedISBN    = 978-1975384104\n | ChapterListCol1 = \n | ChapterListCol2 = \n | Summary         = \n}}\n{{Graphic novel list\n | VolumeNumber    = 11\n | OriginalRelDate = May 18, 2018\n | OriginalISBN    = 978-4091575258\n | LicensedRelDate = June 18, 2019\n | LicensedISBN    = 978-1975304461\n | ChapterListCol1 = \n | ChapterListCol2 = \n | Summary         = \n}}\n{{Graphic novel list\n | VolumeNumber    = 12\n | OriginalRelDate = November 19, 2018\n | OriginalISBN    = 978-4091575500\n | LicensedRelDate = December 17, 2019\n | LicensedISBN    = 978-1975359379\n | ChapterListCol1 = \n | ChapterListCol2 = \n | Summary         = \n}}\n{{Graphic novel list\n | VolumeNumber    = 13\n | OriginalRelDate = April 19, 2019\n | OriginalISBN    = 978-4091575630\n | LicensedRelDate = March 17, 2020\n | LicensedISBN    = 978-1975399504\n | ChapterListCol1 = \n | ChapterListCol2 = \n | Summary         = \n}}\n{{Graphic novel list\n | VolumeNumber    = 14\n | OriginalRelDate = November 19, 2019\n | OriginalISBN    = 978-4091575814\n | LicensedRelDate = \u2014\n | LicensedISBN    = \n | ChapterListCol1 = \n | ChapterListCol2 = \n | Summary         = \n}}\n{{Graphic novel list\n | VolumeNumber    = 15\n | OriginalRelDate = March 19, 2020\n | OriginalISBN    = 978-4091575920\n | LicensedRelDate = \u2014\n | LicensedISBN    = \n | ChapterListCol1 = \n | ChapterListCol2 = \n | Summary         = \n}}\n{{Graphic novel list/footer}}\n\n===Anime===\n{{Main|My Teen Romantic Comedy SNAFU (season 1)|My Teen Romantic Comedy SNAFU (season 2)|My Teen Romantic Comedy SNAFU (season 3)}}\n\nA 13-episode anime television series, directed by Ai Yoshimura and produced by ''[[Brain's Base]]'', aired between April 5 and June 21, 2013,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2013-03-08/my-youth-romantic-comedy-is-wrong-as-i-expected-anime-1st-promo-streamed|title={{'}}''My Youth Romantic Comedy Is Wrong as I Expected''{{'}} Anime's 1st Promo Streamed|date=2013-03-08|accessdate=2013-03-20|work=[[Anime News Network]]}}</ref> with an additional anime-original episode with writing by Wataru Watari following the series on June 27, 2013.<ref name=\"ANN1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2013-05-16/my-teen-romantic-comedy-snafu-gets-more-anime|title=''My Teen Romantic Comedy SNAFU'' Gets More Anime|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=2013-05-16|accessdate=2013-05-17}}</ref> The series was simulcast with English subtitles by [[Crunchyroll]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2013-04-09/crunchyroll-to-stream-my-teen-romantic-comedy-snafu-tv-anime|title=Crunchyroll to Stream {{'}}''My Teen Romantic Comedy SNAFU''{{'}} TV Anime|date=2013-04-09|accessdate=2013-04-09|work=[[Anime News Network]]}}</ref> An [[OVA]] episode on [[Blu-ray Disc]] was bundled with the limited edition of the video game, released on September 19, 2013.<ref name=\"ANN1\" /><ref name=\"ANN2\" />  The opening theme is {{Nihongo|\"Yukitoki\"|\u30e6\u30ad\u30c8\u30ad}} by [[Nagi Yanagi]] and the ending theme is \"Hello Alone\" by [[Saori Hayami]] and [[Nao T\u014dyama]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2013-03-30/my-youth-romantic-comedy-is-wrong-as-i-expected-anime-teaser-posted|title={{'}}''My Youth Romantic Comedy Is Wrong as I Expected''{{'}} Anime's Teaser Posted|date=2013-03-30|accessdate=2013-03-31|work=[[Anime News Network]]}}</ref> The anime has been licensed by [[Sentai Filmworks]] in North America and [[Madman Entertainment]] in Australia and New Zealand.<ref name=\"Official Sentai\">{{cite web|url=http://www.sentaifilmworks.com/shows/my-teen-romantic-comedy-snafu|title=''My Teen Romantic Comedy ~ SNAFU'' - Sentai Filmworks|publisher=[[Section23 Films#Sentai Filmworks|Sentai Filmworks]]|accessdate=September 25, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305202940/http://www.sentaifilmworks.com/shows/my-teen-romantic-comedy-snafu|archive-date=March 5, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Madman Entertainment Acquisitions From Supanova Pop Culture Expo - Gold Coast|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2013-04-21/madman-entertainment-acquisitions-from-supanova-pop-culture-expo-gold-coast|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=2013-04-21|accessdate=2013-04-25}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Sentai Filmworks Adds ''My Teen Romantic Comedy Snafu'' TV Anime|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2013-04-25/sentai-filmworks-adds-my-teen-romantic-comedy-snafu-tv-anime|publisher=Anime News Network|date=2013-04-25|accessdate=2013-04-25}}</ref>\n\nA second season was announced by [[Shogakukan]] in 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2014-04-16/my-teen-romantic-comedy-snafu-anime-gets-2nd-season|title=My Teen Romantic Comedy SNAFU Anime Gets 2nd Season|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=April 16, 2014|accessdate=April 17, 2014}}</ref> The season, titled \"Yahari Ore no Seishun Love Come wa Machigatteiru. Zoku\", is produced by [[Feel (animation studio)|Feel]] and directed by Kei Oikawa, with character designs by Yuichi Tanaka and series composition by Sh\u014dtar\u014d Suga.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2014-10-16/outbreak-company-oikawa-to-direct-my-teen-romantic-comedy-snafu-season-2-at-studio-feel/.80008|title=Outbreak Company's Oikawa to Direct My Teen Romantic Comedy SNAFU Season 2 at Studio feel.|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=October 16, 2014|accessdate=October 16, 2014}}</ref> It aired between April 3 and June 26, 2015. The opening theme is {{nihongo|\"Harumodoki\"|\u6625\u64ec\u304d|}} by Yanagi.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2015-02-22/nagi-yanagi-returns-to-perform-2nd-my-teen-romantic-comedy-snafu-season-opening/.85276|title='Nagi Yanagi Returns to Perform 2nd ''My Teen Romantic Comedy SNAFU'' Season's Opening|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=February 22, 2015|accessdate=April 4, 2015}}</ref> The ending theme is {{nihongo|\"Everyday World.\"|\u30a8\u30d6\u30ea\u30c7\u30a4\u30ef\u30fc\u30eb\u30c9|}} by Yukino Yukinoshita (Hayami) and Yui Yuigahama (T\u014dyama).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2015-03-09/saori-hayami-nao-toyama-return-to-sing-2nd-my-teen-romantic-comedy-snafu-season-ending/.85766|title=Saori Hayami, Nao T\u014dyama Return to Sing 2nd ''My Teen Romantic Comedy SNAFU'' Season's Ending|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=March 9, 2015|accessdate=April 4, 2015}}</ref> The second season has been licensed by Sentai Filmworks.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2015-04-04/sentai-filmworks-adds-pleiades-re-kan-snafu-too-hello-kinmoza-utapri-season-3-is-it-wrong-to-try-to-pick-up-girls-in-a-dungeon-food-wars/.86760|title=Sentai Filmworks Adds ''Pleiades'', ''Re-Kan'', ''Snafu Too'', ''Hello! Kinmoza'', ''UtaPri'' Season 3, ''Is It Wrong to Try to Pick Up Girls in a Dungeon?'', ''Food Wars''|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=April 4, 2014|accessdate=April 4, 2015}}</ref> An [[original video animation|OVA]] episode, titled {{nihongo|''Undoubtedly, Girls Are Made of Sugar, Spice, and Something Nice''|\u304d\u3063\u3068\u3001\u5973\u306e\u5b50\u306f\u304a\u7802\u7cd6\u3068\u30b9\u30d1\u30a4\u30b9\u3068\u7d20\u6575\u306a\u4f55\u304b\u3067\u3067\u304d\u3066\u3044\u308b|Kitto, Onna no Ko wa Osat\u014d to Spice to Suteki na Nanika de Dekiteiru}}, is bundled with the limited edition of the second video game, which was released on October 27, 2016.<ref name=\"OVA2\"/><ref name=\"Game2-Delay\"/>\n\nA third and final season was announced by Shogakukan on March 18, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-03-18/my-teen-romantic-comedy-snafu-tv-anime-gets-3rd-season/.144649|title=My Teen Romantic Comedy SNAFU TV Anime Gets 3rd Season|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=March 18, 2019|accessdate=March 18, 2019}}</ref>  Feel is returning to animate the third season,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-07-04/studio-feel-returns-for-my-teen-romantic-comedy-snafu-tv-anime-3rd-season-in-2020/.148647|title=Studio feel. Returns for My Teen Romantic Comedy SNAFU TV Anime's 3rd Season in 2020|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=July 4, 2019|accessdate=July 4, 2019}}</ref> with Kei Oikawa returning as director, Keiichir\u014d \u014cchi replacing Sh\u014dtar\u014d Suga as series composer, and Yuichi Tanaka returning as character designer. The season, titled \"Yahari Ore no Seishun Love Come wa Machigatteiru. Kan\", was set to premiere on April 9, 2020,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-11-10/my-teen-romantic-comedy-snafu-anime-season-3-video-reveals-cast-staff-title-spring-debut-and-teases-finale/.153126|title=My Teen Romantic Comedy SNAFU Anime Season 3's Video Reveals Cast, Staff, Title, Spring Debut & Teases Finale|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=November 10, 2019|accessdate=November 10, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/daily-briefs/2020-01-27/my-teen-romantic-comedy-snafu-anime-season-3-premieres-on-april-9/.155818|title=My Teen Romantic Comedy SNAFU Anime Season 3 Premieres on April 9|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=January 27, 2020|accessdate=January 27, 2020}}</ref> before the series was delayed due to the ongoing [[coronavirus outbreak]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Harding |first1=Daryl |title=My Teen Romantic Comedy SNAFU Climax TV Anime Broadcast Postponed Due to Coronavirus |url=https://www.crunchyroll.com/anime-news/2020/04/07/my-teen-romantic-comedy-snafu-climax-tv-anime-broadcast-postponed-due-to-coronavirus |website=Crunchyroll |accessdate=7 April 2020 |language=en-us}}</ref> The opening theme is by Yanagi, and the ending theme is by Yukino Yukinoshita (Hayami) and Yui Yuigahama (T\u014dyama).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2020-01-02/my-teen-romantic-comedy-snafu-anime-season-3-reveals-theme-songs/.154991|title=My Teen Romantic Comedy SNAFU Anime Season 3 Reveals Theme Songs|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=January 2, 2020|accessdate=January 27, 2020}}</ref> Sentai Filmworks licensed the third season globally excluding Asia.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sentaifilmworks.com/a/news/sentai-snaps-up-season-3-of-my-teen-romantic-comedy-snafu|title=SENTAI SNAPS UP SEASON 3 OF \"MY TEEN ROMANTIC COMEDY SNAFU\"|date=March 30, 2020|publisher=[[Sentai Filmworks]]|accessdate=March 31, 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn April 2, 2019, Sentai Filmworks confirmed on Twitter that the series will receive a dub.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/SentaiFilmworks/status/1112974197582696448|title=#AprilTruth: My Teen Romantic Comedy SNAFU dub is coming... (promise)|last=Filmworks|first=Sentai|date=2019-04-02|website=@SentaiFilmworks|language=en|access-date=2019-04-02}}</ref> On July 5, Sentai announced both seasons 1 and 2 will be dubbed.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-07-04/both-seasons-of-my-teen-romantic-comedy-snafu-anime-get-english-dub/.148616|title=Both Seasons of My Teen Romantic Comedy SNAFU Anime Get English Dub|website=Anime News Network|language=en|access-date=2019-07-05}}</ref>\n\n===Video games===\nA video game for [[PlayStation Vita]], titled {{Nihongo|''Yahari Game demo Ore no Seishun Rabu Kome wa Machigatteiru.''|\u3084\u306f\u308a\u30b2\u30fc\u30e0\u3067\u3082\u4ffa\u306e\u9752\u6625\u30e9\u30d6\u30b3\u30e1\u306f\u307e\u3061\u304c\u3063\u3066\u3044\u308b\u3002|lit. \"My Youth Romantic Comedy even in Game is Wrong As I Expected.\"}} was published by [[5pb.]] and released on September 19, 2013. Takuya Eguchi, Saori Hayami, and Nao T\u014dyama reprised their roles from the anime.<ref name=\"ANN2\">{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2013-06-05/my-teen-romantic-comedy-snafu-game-ova-to-ship-on-september-19|title=''My Teen Romantic Comedy SNAFU'' Game, OVA to Ship on September 19|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=June 5, 2013|accessdate=2013-06-07}}</ref> The limited edition was bundled with an OVA episode.<ref name=\"ANN1\" /> 5pb. developed a second video game for the series for the PlayStation Vita that adapted the second season of the anime television series.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2015-06-07/5pb-develops-my-teen-romantic-comedy-snafu-video-game-sequel/.89015|title=5pb. Develops ''My Teen Romantic Comedy SNAFU'' Video Game Sequel|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=June 7, 2015|accessdate=June 8, 2015}}</ref><ref>http://gematsu.com/2015/08/my-teen-romantic-comedy-snafu-too-game-confirmed-ps-vita</ref> It was released on October 27, 2016. Like the first game, the limited edition was bundled with an OVA episode.<ref name=\"OVA2\">{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-04-08/my-teen-romantic-comedy-snafu-too-ps-vita-game-to-bundle-original-anime-blu-ray/.100842|title=My Teen Romantic Comedy SNAFU TOO! PS Vita Game to Bundle Original Anime Blu-ray|date=April 8, 2016|website=[[Anime News Network]]|accessdate=April 8, 2016}}</ref> The release date of the second game was postponed from July 28, 2016 to October 27, 2016 on June 14, 2016.<ref name=\"Game2-Delay\">{{cite web|url=http://5pb.jp/games/topics/7513.html|title=PS Vita\u300e\u3084\u306f\u308a\u30b2\u30fc\u30e0\u3067\u3082\u4ffa\u306e\u9752\u6625\u30e9\u30d6\u30b3\u30e1\u306f\u307e\u3061\u304c\u3063\u3066\u3044\u308b\u3002\u7d9a\u300f\u767a\u58f2\u65e5\u5ef6\u671f\u306e\u304a\u8a6b\u3073\u3068\u304a\u77e5\u3089\u305b|date=June 14, 2016|accessdate=June 16, 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n''My Youth Romantic Comedy Is Wrong, As I Expected'' was chosen as the best light novel of Japan according to the online polls compiled by the ''[[Kono Light Novel ga Sugoi!]]'' annual guide book in 2014, 2015 and 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2014-11-12/my-teen-romantic-comedy-snafu-tops-kono-light-novel-ga-sugoi-list-for-2nd-straight-year/.80934|title=My Teen Romantic Comedy SNAFU Tops Kono Light Novel ga Sugoi! List for 2nd Straight Year|work=[[Anime News Network]]|date=November 11, 2014|accessdate=November 19, 2016}}</ref> Hachiman Hikigaya was elected the best male character in 2014, 2015 and 2016, Yukino Yukinoshita was elected the best female character in 2015 and Ponkan8, the series' artist, was chosen as the best illustrator in 2015 and 2016.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://gagagabunko.jp/specal/oregairu/ Light novel official website] {{in lang|ja}}\n* [http://www.tbs.co.jp/anime/oregairu Anime official website] {{in lang|ja}}\n* [http://5pb.jp/games/oregairu Video game official website] {{in lang|ja}}\n* {{ann|light novel|17263}}\n\n{{Gangan Comics manga franchises}}\n{{Monthly Sunday Gene-X}}\n{{Brain's Base}}\n{{Feel}}\n\n[[Category:2011 Japanese novels]]\n[[Category:2012 manga]]\n[[Category:2013 anime television series]]\n[[Category:2015 anime television series]]\n[[Category:Upcoming anime television series]]\n[[Category:Anime and manga based on light novels]]\n[[Category:Brain's Base]]\n[[Category:Feel (company)]]\n[[Category:Gagaga Bunko]]\n[[Category:Gangan Comics manga]]\n[[Category:Ichijinsha manga]]\n[[Category:Light novels]]\n[[Category:NBCUniversal Entertainment Japan]]\n[[Category:Romantic comedy anime and manga]]\n[[Category:School life in anime and manga]]\n[[Category:Seinen manga]]\n[[Category:Sentai Filmworks]]\n[[Category:Shogakukan franchises]]\n[[Category:Shogakukan manga]]\n[[Category:Slice of life anime and manga]]\n[[Category:Television programs based on light novels]]\n[[Category:Tokyo Broadcasting System shows]]\n[[Category:Yen Press titles]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox animanga/Header\n| name            = My Youth Romantic Comedy Is Wrong, As I Expected\n| image           = My Teen Romantic Comedy SNAFU cover.jpg\n| caption         = Cover of the first light novel volume, featuring Hachiman Hikigaya and Yukino Yukinoshita\n| ja_kanji        = \u3084\u306f\u308a\u4ffa\u306e\u9752\u6625\u30e9\u30d6\u30b3\u30e1\u306f\u307e\u3061\u304c\u3063\u3066\u3044\u308b\u3002\n| ja_romaji       = Yahari Ore no Seishun Rabukome wa Machigatteiru.\n| genre           = [[Romance novel|Romance]], [[comedy]], [[slice of life]]<ref name=\"Official Sentai\"/><!-- Genres should be based on what reliable sources list them as and not on personal interpretations. Limit of the three most relevant genres in accordance with [[MOS:A&M]]. -->\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Print\n| type            = light novel\n| author          = Wataru Watari\n| illustrator     = Ponkan8\n| publisher       = [[Shogakukan]]\n| publisher_en    = {{English manga publisher|NA =[[Yen Press]]}}\n| demographic     = Male\n| imprint         = [[Gagaga Bunko]]\n| first           = March 18, 2011\n| last            = November 19, 2019\n| volumes         = 14 + 3 short story collections\n| volume_list     = #Light novels\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Print\n| type            = manga\n| title           = My Youth Romantic Comedy Is Wrong, As I Expected -Monologue-\n| author          = Rechi Kazuki\n| publisher       = [[Square Enix]]\n| demographic     = ''[[Seinen manga|Seinen]]''\n| magazine        = Big Gangan\n| first           = September 25, 2012\n| last            = \n| volumes         = 16\n| volume_list     = #My Youth Romantic Comedy Is Wrong, As I Expected -Monologue- volumes\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Print\n| type            = manga\n| title           = My Youth Romantic Comedy Is Wrong, As I Expected @ comic\n| author          = Naomichi Io\n| publisher       = Shogakukan\n| publisher_en    = {{English manga publisher|NA =[[Yen Press]]}}\n| demographic     = ''Seinen''\n| magazine        = [[Monthly Sunday Gene-X]]\n| first           = December 19, 2012\n| last            = \n| volumes         = 15\n| volume_list     = #My Youth Romantic Comedy Is Wrong, As I Expected @comic volumes\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Print\n| type            = manga\n| title           = Yahari 4-koma demo Ore no Seishun Rabu Kome wa machigatteiru.\n| author          = Y\u016bta Taneda\n| publisher       = [[Ichijinsha]]\n| demographic     = ''Seinen''\n| magazine        = Manga 4-koma Palette\n| first           = April 22, 2013\n| last            = June 22, 2015\n| volumes         = 2\n| volume_list     = \n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Video\n| title           = My Teen Romantic Comedy SNAFU\n| type            = TV series\n| director        = Ai Yoshimura\n| writer          = Sh\u014dtar\u014d Suga\n| music           = Kakeru Ishihama <small>(Monaca)</small>\n| studio          = [[Brain's Base]]\n| licensee        = {{English anime licensee\n | AUS = [[Madman Entertainment]]\n | NA  = [[Sentai Filmworks]]\n | UK=[[Animatsu Entertainment]]\n}}\n| network         = [[Tokyo Broadcasting System|TBS]], [[Mainichi Broadcasting System|MBS]], [[Chubu-Nippon Broadcasting|CBC]], [[BS-TBS]]\n| network_en      = {{English anime network\n |NA=[[Anime Network]]\n |SEA=[[Animax Asia]]\n}}\n| first           = April 5, 2013\n| last            = June 28, 2013\n| episodes        = 13 + OVA\n| episode_list    = My Teen Romantic Comedy SNAFU (season 1)\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Game\n| title           = Yahari Game demo Ore no Seishun Rabukome wa Machigatteiru.\n| developer       = [[5pb.]]\n| publisher       = 5pb.\n| genre           = \n| platforms       = [[PlayStation Vita]]\n| released        = {{vgrelease|JP|September 19, 2013}}\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Video\n| title           = My Teen Romantic Comedy SNAFU TOO!\n| type            = TV series\n| director        = Kei Oikawa\n| writer          = Sh\u014dtar\u014d Suga\n| music           = Kakeru Ishihama <small>(Monaca)</small><br/>Kuniyuki Takahashi <small>(Monaca)</small>\n| studio          = [[Feel (animation studio)|Feel]]\n| licensee        = {{English anime licensee\n | AUS = Madman Entertainment\n | NA  = Sentai Filmworks\n | UK=Animatsu Entertainment\n}}\n| network         = TBS, CBC, [[Tulip Television|TUT]], MBS, BS-TBS\n| network_en      = {{English anime network\n  |NA=[[Anime Network]]\n}}\n| first           = April 3, 2015\n| last            = June 26, 2015\n| episodes        = 13 + OVA\n| episode_list    = My Teen Romantic Comedy SNAFU (season 2)\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Game\n| title           = Yahari Game demo Ore no Seishun Rabukome wa Machigatteiru. Zoku\n| developer       = [[5pb.]]\n| publisher       = 5pb.\n| genre           = \n| platforms       = [[PlayStation Vita]]\n| released        = {{vgrelease|JP|October 27, 2016}}\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Video\n| title           = My Teen Romantic Comedy SNAFU Climax\n| type            = TV series\n| director        = Kei Oikawa\n| writer          = Keiichir\u014d \u014cchi\n| music           = Kakeru Ishihama <small>(Monaca)</small><br/>Kuniyuki Takahashi <small>(Monaca)</small>\n| studio          = Feel\n| licensee        = Sentai Filmworks <!-- Worldwide excluding Asia -->\n| network         = TBS, MBS, CBC,  BS-TBS\n| first           = \n| last            = \n| episodes        = \n| episode_list    = \n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Footer}}\n\n{{Nihongo|'''''My Youth Romantic Comedy Is Wrong, As I Expected'''''|\u3084\u306f\u308a\u4ffa\u306e\u9752\u6625\u30e9\u30d6\u30b3\u30e1\u306f\u307e\u3061\u304c\u3063\u3066\u3044\u308b\u3002|Yahari Ore no Seishun Rabukome wa Machigatteiru.|lead=yes}}, abbreviated as {{nihongo|'''''OreGairu'''''|\u4ffa\u30ac\u30a4\u30eb}} and {{nihongo|'''''Hamachi'''''|\u306f\u307e\u3061}},<ref>{{cite web|url=http://d.hatena.ne.jp/watariwataru/20110215/1297794528|script-title=ja:\u300e\u3084\u306f\u308a\u4ffa\u306e\u9752\u6625\u30e9\u30d6\u30b3\u30e1\u306f\u307e\u3061\u304c\u3063\u3066\u3044\u308b\u3002\u300f\u7565\u79f0\u3092\u8003\u3048\u308b\u30b3\u30fc\u30ca\u30fc|language=Japanese|publisher=Wataru Watari|date=2011-02-15|accessdate=2013-01-10|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6FhCQlmRa?url=http://d.hatena.ne.jp/watariwataru/20110215/1297794528|archivedate=2013-04-07}}</ref> and also known as '''''My Teen Romantic Comedy SNAFU''''', is a Japanese [[light novel]] series written by Wataru Watari and illustrated by Ponkan8. The series follows Hachiman Hikigaya, a pessimistic, closeminded, and realistic teen, who is forced by his teacher to join the school's service club and work with two girls with issues of their own. They offer help and advice to others while dealing with their inner conflicts.\n\nThere are three manga adaptations and two [[anthology]] volumes. It has been adapted into an [[anime]] television series, which aired between April 4 and June 27, 2013 and was followed by a second season which aired between April 2 and June 25, 2015, as well as an upcoming third and final season. ''Yahari Game demo Ore no Seishun Rabukome wa Machigatteiru'', a video game was released by [[5pb.]], for the [[PlayStation Vita]] was released on September 19, 2013. A second video game also by 5pb was released on October 27, 2016.\n\n==Characters==\n===Main characters===\nThe main characters in the series are members of the school's service club, which is run by Yukino Yukinoshita.\n\n;{{Nihongo|Hachiman Hikigaya|\u6bd4\u4f01\u8c37 \u516b\u5e61|Hikigaya Hachiman}}{{anchor|Hachiman Hikigaya}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Takuya Eguchi]]|[[Adam Gibbs]]<ref name=\"Dub cast\">{{cite web|url=https://www.sentaifilmworks.com/a/news/my-romantic-comedy-snafu-official-english-cast-list|title=My Romantic Comedy SNAFU Official English Cast List|work=[[Sentai Filmworks]]|date=September 16, 2019|accessdate=September 16, 2019}}</ref>}}\n: The [[viewpoint character]] of the light novels, Hachiman is a student in class 2F of S\u014dbu High School who has been discriminated in the past to the point that he becomes isolated, friendless, and pragmatic to a fault. His most prominent feature is his set of \"dead fish-eyes\" that puts people off. Due to years of social isolation, he has developed a habit of observing people in his surroudings from a distance, earning him a skill for social perception, figuring out the true nature of people. He believes that youth is an illusion created by hypocrites, for hypocrites, born from his past failures. His experience leads him to believe the happiness of others is a facade. He is affectionately called \"Hikki\" by Yui. Hayato's clique wrongly address him as \"Hikitani\".\n\n: His teacher Shizuka worries about him becoming a social outcast and forces him to join the Service Club. Hachiman believes himself to be an insignificant entity and is willing to take the blame in order to keep everyone else happy.\n: On the first day of high school, he winds up in a car accident from trying to save Yui's puppy and ends up in the hospital for three weeks, making him an outsider once he gets back because the whole class has already formed its cliques. He thinks that Yui's feelings for him are due to guilt and thus, indirectly rejects Yui, thinking he would cause trouble for her. He also distances himself from Yukino after realizing that the car that rammed into him belongs to her family. In both cases, they make amends with him once said misunderstandings are cleared. It is suggested that he is aware of the girl's feelings, due to studying people's behavior and doesn't accept them as genuine.\n;{{Nihongo|Yukino Yukinoshita|\u96ea\u30ce\u4e0b \u96ea\u4e43|Yukinoshita Yukino}}{{anchor|Yukino Yukinoshita}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Saori Hayami]]|Melissa Molano<ref name=\"Dub cast\" />}}\n: Yukino is a student in class 2J and the leader of the Service Club but was the sole member until Hachiman joined. Born to a wealthy family, she is smart, beautiful, and nicknamed the \"Ice-cold Beauty\" for her icy demeanour. She shows no empathy and little kindness towards Hachiman at first, but eventually opens up to him. Due to her talent and beauty, she is envied by most girls and is disgusted by their attitude to undermine her instead of improving themselves, thus she has few friends. She has a twisted sense of ''noblesse oblige'', and believes it is the duty of the exceptional to help the \"lost lambs\" of the world. She essentially wants to help others, but is brutally honest and directly analyses their flaws. Her personality often leads her to be disgusted at the naivet\u00e9 and lack of understanding how things work of others, particularly Yui's, and she does not hesitate to show it. Despite this, Yui still affectionately refers to her as \"Yukinon\"; thanks to her, Yukino becomes kinder and the two girls become best friends. She recognizes Hachiman from the car accident but lies about it when Hachiman joins the Service Club. She is devastated when he distances himself from her, after learning it from her sister. Throughout the series, she develops feelings for him.\n;{{nihongo|Yui Yuigahama|\u7531\u6bd4\u30f6\u6d5c \u7d50\u8863|Yuigahama Yui}}{{anchor|Yui Yuigahama}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Nao T\u014dyama]]|Cat Thomas<ref name=\"Dub cast\" />}}\n: Yui is Hachiman's classmate. A cheerful, outgoing girl, she becomes the Service Club's first \"customer,\" asking them to help her bake cookies for \"a certain someone.\" By no means cynical and the friendliest member of the group, her problems lie not with her personality, but with her inability to express herself due to fear of losing friends, and thus admires Yukino and Hachiman, who are able to express their true feelings. She believes that talent is inborn, and often aspires to be like others until Yukino changes her way of thinking. Following her experience with the Service Club, Yui begins to attend Service Club sessions after school as well, despite Yukino's objections early on. In class, Yui is a member of Hayato's clique but has no say in matters as she is often overwhelmed by Yumiko. She has been holding feelings towards Hachiman ever since he saved her dog on the first day of high school.\n\n===Class 2F===\n;{{Nihongo|Saika Totsuka|\u6238\u585a \u5f69\u52a0|Totsuka Saika}}{{anchor|Saika Totsuka}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Mikako Komatsu]]|[[Margaret McDonald (voice actress)|Margaret McDonald]]<ref name=\"Dub cast\" />}}\n: Saika is the president of the tennis club who has an [[androgyny|androgynous appearance]] but prefers others to not mistake his gender. He is called \"The Prince\" by his female classmates. On their first meeting, Saika asks help from Hachiman to join the tennis club, which was brushed off by Yukino. Saika then asked the Service Club to help him improve his tennis skills. He eventually became one of the few people in class 2F who would talk to Hachiman on a first name basis, and often hangs out with him. Despite knowing that Saika is a boy, Hachiman oftentimes finds himself unwillingly attracted to him.\n;{{Nihongo|Hayato Hayama|\u8449\u5c71 \u96bc\u4eba|Hayama Hayato}}{{anchor|Hayato Hayama}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Takashi Kond\u014d]]|Scott Gibbs<ref name=\"Dub cast\" />}}\n: Hayato is Yukino's childhood friend who is a central figure in class 2F and the ace of the football club. He is extremely kind to other people, including Hachiman, and often offers his help to others. However, Hayama claims that he can never forge a good relationship with Hachiman since, despite understanding his acts of social suicide to protect everyone, he does not agree with him. He and Yukino have some strain to their relationship, stemming from an incident in the past, and thus far, his attempts to mend his relationship with Yukino have failed. Despite his popularity and success, he feels largely inferior to Hachiman.\n;{{Nihongo|Yumiko Miura|\u4e09\u6d66 \u512a\u7f8e\u5b50|Miura Yumiko}}{{anchor|Yumiko Miura}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Marina Inoue]]|[[Christina Kelly]]<ref name=\"Dub cast\" />}}\n: Yumiko is a popular girl from class 2F with a pompous personality. She is the main female figure in Hayato's clique and it is hinted that she has feelings for Hayato. Due to her popularity, she has no trouble making friends, and thus has little to no understanding towards people who have social troubles. \n;{{Nihongo|Hina Ebina|\u6d77\u8001\u540d \u59eb\u83dc|Ebina Hina}}{{anchor|Hina Ebina}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Nozomi Sasaki (voice actress)|Nozomi Sasaki]]|Natalie Rial<ref name=\"Dub cast\" />}}.\n:A close friend of Yumiko and Yui's, and a member of Hayato's clique. A massive Yaoi fangirl who loves to see two boys hitting on each other. When she gets riled up, all respect for personal space of others goes out the window. She has an eye for detail, especially for clothing.\n;{{Nihongo|Saki Kawasaki|\u5ddd\u5d0e \u6c99\u5e0c|Kawasaki Saki}}{{anchor|Saki Kawasaki}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Ami Koshimizu]]|Teresa Zimmermann<ref name=\"Dub cast\" />}}\n: Saki is Hachiman's classmate who seems like a delinquent but wants to make friends deep down. She cares deeply for her brother as she hid her name and age to work as a night-shift bartender in order to pay school fees and reduce her family's load. After her brother asked for the Service Club's help, they eventually followed Saki to her workplace and found out her motives behind working night-shifts; she stopped working after the Service Club suggested her to aim for a scholarship instead.\n;{{Nihongo|Kakeru Tobe|\u6238\u90e8 \u7fd4|Tobe Kakeru}}{{anchor|Kakeru Tobe}}\n:{{voiced by|Chado Horii|Gareth West<ref name=\"Dub cast\" />}}\n: Tobe is a member of Hayato's clique who is in the football club. He has feelings for Hina and is the only guy in the class who supported Hina's script for the cultural festival. During the school excursion, he intended to confess to Hina and therefore requested help from the Service Club. However, Hachiman knew Hina did not want to get into a relationship, so he confesses to (and is rejected by) Hina to prevent Tobe from being rejected, thus maintaining the status quo within that group. \n;{{Nihongo|Yamato|\u5927\u548c|Yamato}}{{anchor|Yamato}}\n:{{voiced by|Yoshihisa Kawahara|Orlanders Jones<ref name=\"Dub cast\" />}}\n: Yamato is a member of Hayato's clique who is in the rugby club.\n;{{Nihongo|\u014coka|\u5927\u5ca1|\u014coka}}{{anchor|\u014coka}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Minoru Shiraishi]]|Daniel Regojo<ref name=\"Dub cast\" />}}\n: \u014coka is a member of Hayato's clique who is in the baseball club.\n;{{Nihongo|Minami Sagami|\u76f8\u6a21 \u5357|Sagami Minami}}{{anchor|Minami Sagami}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Minako Kotobuki]]|[[Caitlynn French]]<ref name=\"Dub cast\" />}}\n: Minami is the leader of the second most influential clique in class 2F and holds a grudge towards Yui, who she was friendly with during their first high school year, for being in the superior clique. She volunteered to be event organizer for the cultural festival in order to promote her worth without the actual ability to do such a job, and thus requested help from the Service Club. As such, Yukino took up the role of an assistant event organizer and claimed the spotlight in making the cultural festival a successful one, which in turn made Minami depressed about her own uselessness and refused to host the closing ceremony. However, as Hachiman's fierce scolding has successfully turned himself into the scapegoat and shifted the blame away from Minami, she attended the closing ceremony and ended the cultural festival on a high note.\n\n===Others===\n;{{Nihongo|Shizuka Hiratsuka|\u5e73\u585a \u9759|Hiratsuka Shizuka}}{{anchor|Shizuka Hiratsuka}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Ryoka Yuzuki]]|Heidi Hinkel<ref name=\"Dub cast\" />}}\n: Shizuka is Hachiman's teacher, a language teacher who serves as his futures advisor/ counsellor and the consultant for the service club. She is aware of Hachiman's supposed \"problems\", and takes steps to ensure he is freed from them, her first move being to force him into joining the Service Club. However, she appears to have some quirks of her own: she is a young smoker, she is very sensitive about her age and single status, and she is often prone to quoting or copying scenes from popular [[sh\u014dnen manga]]. Additionally, she never remembers to knock before entering the Service Club's classroom, much to Yukino's chagrin. After the cultural festival incident, she tells Hachiman that helping others should not be a reason for Hachiman to hurt himself, as there are others who would feel pain seeing Hachiman hurt.\n;{{Nihongo|Komachi Hikigaya|\u6bd4\u4f01\u8c37 \u5c0f\u753a|Hikigaya Komachi}}{{anchor|Komachi Hikigaya}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Aoi Y\u016bki]]|[[Hilary Haag]]<ref name=\"Dub cast\" />}}\n: Komachi is Hachiman's younger sister who, different from her brother, is cheerful and lively, and is a member of the student council in her school. She understands her brother's anti-social personality, cares for, and relies on him. While attached to her brother, she shows cleverness in trying to pair up Hachiman with Yukino or Yui.\n;{{Nihongo|Yoshiteru Zaimokuza|\u6750\u6728\u5ea7 \u7fa9\u8f1d|Zaimokuza Yoshiteru}}{{anchor|Yoshiteru Zaimokuza}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Nobuyuki Hiyama]]|Andrew Love<ref name=\"Dub cast\" />}}\n: Yoshiteru is a student from class 2C who suffers from adolescent delusions. He sees Hachiman as a friend after being paired up with him during physical education lessons. While he is annoying, he has a group of [[otaku]] friends he's on good terms with. He aims to be a light novel writer.\n;{{Nihongo|Haruno Yukinoshita|\u96ea\u30ce\u4e0b \u967d\u4e43|Yukinoshita Haruno}}{{anchor|Haruno Yukinoshita}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Mai Nakahara]]|Olivia Swasey<ref name=\"Dub cast\" />}}\n: Haruno is Yukino's elder sister. Unlike Yukino, she shows a good attitude towards other people at first but eventually shows a sinister personality. Despite being a college student she spends a good deal of time spying on her sister's life. Yukino holds strong animosity towards her and Haruno can only say her sister constantly tries to overtake her as cute. Nonetheless, Haruno eventually shows her own grudges against Yukino and makes Yukino and Hachiman feel bad in the 2nd season.\n: She is a former student of S\u014dbu High School. She acknowledges Hachiman's perceptiveness and often playfully teases him.\n: Her being beautiful, rich, and charismatic makes people (including the series' audience) only see her good side, defer to her and ignore big problems she causes to others. For instance, in the 1st season, Haruno appears suddenly to abruptly intervene with the Cultural Festival where her role becomes to encourage the President to take it easy, resulting in delayed tasks. Hachiman takes part in picking up the slack and assumes his usual blame-taking role by complaining for the sake of others, complaints that only get him criticized, leading him to a dramatic confrontation with the Festival President.\n;{{Nihongo|Taishi Kawasaki|\u5ddd\u5d0e \u5927\u5fd7|Kawasaki Taishi}}{{anchor|Taishi Kawasaki}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Ayumu Murase]]|Morgan Berry<ref name=\"Dub cast\" />}}\n: Taishi is Saki's little brother and Komachi's classmate. He is on good terms with Komachi and is worried about Saki coming home late every night.\n;{{Nihongo|Rumi Tsurumi|\u9db4\u898b \u7559\u7f8e|Tsurumi Rumi}}{{anchor|Rumi Tsurumi}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Sumire Morohoshi]]|Savanna Menzel<ref name=\"Dub cast\" />}}\n: Rumi is a lonely primary school student who is openly despised by her peers. Hayato at first tried to resolve the situation through talking to her in front of her classmates, which instead attracted more hateful attention to her. Hachiman and company decided that the only way out is to destroy the trust between her peers, through having Hayato and Kakeru acting as bullies threatening Rumi's group-mates during treasure hunt. However, Rumi was able to use her camera's flash as a distraction, allowing the group to escape. \n;{{Nihongo|Meguri Shiromeguri|\u57ce\u5efb \u3081\u3050\u308a|Shiromeguri Meguri}}{{anchor|Meguri Shiromeguri}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Azumi Asakura]]|[[Jad Saxton]]<ref name=\"Dub cast\" />}}\n: Meguri is a third-year student and the former president of S\u014dbu High School's student council. Although she is not a reliable leader herself, her personality has brought her immense support from the councillors and thus she is able to unite the student council.\n;{{Nihongo|Iroha Isshiki|\u4e00\u8272 \u3044\u308d\u306f|Isshiki Iroha}}{{anchor|Iroha Isshiki}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Ayane Sakura]]|[[Luci Christian]]<ref name=\"Dub 2 cast\">{{cite web|url=https://www.sentaifilmworks.com/a/news/my-romantic-comedy-snafu-too-official-english-cast-list|title=My Romantic Comedy SNAFU TOO! Official English Cast List|work=[[Sentai Filmworks]]|date=September 16, 2019|accessdate=September 16, 2019}}</ref>}}\n: Iroha is a first-year student who manages the football team, is cheerful and pretty. As she was recommended as a candidate for the student council president in a prank, out of her dislike of the role, she filed a request to the Service Club in order to not get elected and yet not lose in an embarrassing fashion. She eventually accepts her role of being the student council president after Hachiman managed to convince her. There is a running joke where Iroha mistakes something that Hachiman says or does as flirting, and promptly rejects him.\n;{{Nihongo|Kaori Orimoto|\u6298\u672c \u304b\u304a\u308a|Orimoto Kaori}}{{anchor|Kaori Orimoto}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Haruka Tomatsu]]|[[Kira Vincent-Davis]]<ref name=\"Dub 2 cast\" />}}\n: Kaori is Hachiman's classmate in middle school, whom he confessed to in the past. She attends Kaihin General High School.\n;{{Nihongo|Chika Nakamachi|\u4ef2\u753a \u5343\u4f73|Nakamachi Chika}}{{anchor|Chika Nakamachi}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Saki Fujita]]|Christie Guidry<ref name=\"Dub 2 cast\" />}}\n:Chika is Kaori's friend and schoolmate at Kaihin General. She is interested in Hayato.\n;{{Nihongo|Tamanawa|\u7389\u7e04|}}{{anchor|Tamanawa}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Satoshi Hino]]|Mike Haimoto<ref name=\"Dub 2 cast\" />}}\n:Tamanawa is Kaihin High School's student council president.\n; Mrs. Yukinoshita\n:{{voiced by|[[Kikuko Inoue]]|[[Shelley Calene-Black]]<ref name=\"Dub 2 cast\" />}}\n: She is Haruno and Yukino's mother. She worries for Yukino's whereabouts living alone and has Haruno spy on her. She is disappointed when she runs into Yukino late at night after a student council event.\n; Mrs. Yuigahama\n:{{voiced by|[[Sayaka Ohara]]|[[Monica Rial]]<ref name=\"Dub 2 cast\" />}}\n: She is Yui's mother and has a close mother-daughter relationship with Yui, one which Yukino is envious of.\n\n==Media==\n\n===Light novels===\nThe light novel series is written by Wataru Watari and illustrated by Ponkan8. It is being published by ''[[Shogakukan]]'' under the ''[[Gagaga Bunko]]'' imprint. The first volume was published on March 18, 2011<ref name=\"ln1\" /> and the series was concluded with its 14th volume released on November 19, 2019.<ref name=ln14 />\n\nVolumes 3, 4, 7, and 8 were published simultaneously with limited special editions. The special editions of the 3rd and 7th volumes were bundled with drama CDs<ref name=\"ln3_le\" /><ref name=\"ln7_le\" /> and those of the 4th and 8th volumes \u2013 with art books by Ponkan8 and guest illustrators.<ref name=\"ln4_le\" /><ref name=\"ln8_le\" /> A set of the first 7 volumes was released on March 19, 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.co.jp/dp/B00BOH6TN0|script-title=ja:\u3084\u306f\u308a\u4ffa\u306e\u9752\u6625\u30e9\u30d6\u30b3\u30e1\u306f\u307e\u3061\u304c\u3063\u3066\u3044\u308b\u3002 \u6587\u5eab 1-7\u5dfb\u30bb\u30c3\u30c8 (\u30ac\u30ac\u30ac\u6587\u5eab)|language=Japanese|publisher=[[Amazon.co.jp]]|accessdate=2013-06-09}}</ref> A collection of short stories, volume 7.5, was published on August 20, 2013.<ref name=ln7.5 /> Three additional short volumes, 6.25, 6.50 and 6.75 were bundled with the limited editions of the 1st, 3rd and 5th DVD and BD volumes respectively of the first anime series,<ref name=bd1>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.co.jp/dp/B00CA0C4YS|title=\u3084\u306f\u308a\u4ffa\u306e\u9752\u6625\u30e9\u30d6\u30b3\u30e1\u306f\u307e\u3061\u304c\u3063\u3066\u3044\u308b\u3002\u7b2c1\u5dfb (\u521d\u56de\u9650\u5b9a\u7248)(\u6e21 \u822a\u66f8\u304d\u4e0b\u308d\u3057\u6587\u5eab\u5c0f\u8aac152P\u30fb\u30b5\u30f3\u30c8\u30e9CD\u540c\u68b1) [Blu-ray] (2013)|language=Japanese|publisher=[[Amazon.co.jp]]|accessdate=2013-08-20}}</ref><ref name=bd3>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.co.jp/dp/B00CBDFTW8|title=\u3084\u306f\u308a\u4ffa\u306e\u9752\u6625\u30e9\u30d6\u30b3\u30e1\u306f\u307e\u3061\u304c\u3063\u3066\u3044\u308b\u3002\u7b2c3\u5dfb (\u521d\u56de\u9650\u5b9a\u7248) [Blu-ray]|language=Japanese|publisher=[[Amazon.co.jp]]|accessdate=2013-08-20}}</ref><ref name=bd5>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.co.jp/dp/B00CBDFUW2|title=\u3084\u306f\u308a\u4ffa\u306e\u9752\u6625\u30e9\u30d6\u30b3\u30e1\u306f\u307e\u3061\u304c\u3063\u3066\u3044\u308b\u3002\u7b2c5\u5dfb (\u521d\u56de\u9650\u5b9a\u7248) [Blu-ray]|language=Japanese|publisher=[[Amazon.co.jp]]|accessdate=2013-08-20}}</ref> and were released as single volume, numbered 6.5, on July 22, 2014.<ref name=ln6.5_re /> A limited special edition of it was bundled with a drama CD.<ref name=ln6.5_le /> Another short story collection volume, labeled 10.5, was released on March 18, 2015.<ref name=ln10.5 />\n\n{{Graphic novel list/header\n | Language        = Japanese\n | SecondLanguage  = English\n | LineColor       = CCF\n}}\n{{Graphic novel list\n| VolumeNumber = 1\n| OriginalRelDate = March 18, 2011<ref name=\"ln1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.co.jp/dp/4094512624|script-title=ja:\u3084\u306f\u308a\u4ffa\u306e\u9752\u6625\u30e9\u30d6\u30b3\u30e1\u306f\u307e\u3061\u304c\u3063\u3066\u3044\u308b\u3002 (\u30ac\u30ac\u30ac\u6587\u5eab)|language=Japanese|publisher=[[Amazon.co.jp]]|accessdate=2013-06-09}}</ref>\n| OriginalISBN = 978-4-09-451262-5\n| LicensedRelDate = September 27, 2016<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hachettebookgroup.com/titles/none/My-Youth-Romantic-Comedy-Is-Wrong-As-I-Expected-Vol-1/9780316312295/?yen |title=My Youth Romantic Comedy Is Wrong, As I Expected, Vol. 1 |website=[[Hachette Book Group]] |access