aphic novel list\n | VolumeNumber    = 11\n | OriginalRelDate = May 18, 2018\n | OriginalISBN    = 978-4091575258\n | LicensedRelDate = June 18, 2019\n | LicensedISBN    = 978-1975304461\n | ChapterListCol1 = \n | ChapterListCol2 = \n | Summary         = \n}}\n{{Graphic novel list\n | VolumeNumber    = 12\n | OriginalRelDate = November 19, 2018\n | OriginalISBN    = 978-4091575500\n | LicensedRelDate = December 17, 2019\n | LicensedISBN    = 978-1975359379\n | ChapterListCol1 = \n | ChapterListCol2 = \n | Summary         = \n}}\n{{Graphic novel list\n | VolumeNumber    = 13\n | OriginalRelDate = April 19, 2019\n | OriginalISBN    = 978-4091575630\n | LicensedRelDate = March 17, 2020\n | LicensedISBN    = 978-1975399504\n | ChapterListCol1 = \n | ChapterListCol2 = \n | Summary         = \n}}\n{{Graphic novel list\n | VolumeNumber    = 14\n | OriginalRelDate = November 19, 2019\n | OriginalISBN    = 978-4091575814\n | LicensedRelDate = \u2014\n | LicensedISBN    = \n | ChapterListCol1 = \n | ChapterListCol2 = \n | Summary         = \n}}\n{{Graphic novel list\n | VolumeNumber    = 15\n | OriginalRelDate = March 19, 2020\n | OriginalISBN    = 978-4091575920\n | LicensedRelDate = \u2014\n | LicensedISBN    = \n | ChapterListCol1 = \n | ChapterListCol2 = \n | Summary         = \n}}\n{{Graphic novel list/footer}}\n\n===Anime===\n{{Main|My Teen Romantic Comedy SNAFU (season 1)|My Teen Romantic Comedy SNAFU (season 2)|My Teen Romantic Comedy SNAFU (season 3)}}\n\nA 13-episode anime television series, directed by Ai Yoshimura and produced by ''[[Brain's Base]]'', aired between April 5 and June 21, 2013,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2013-03-08/my-youth-romantic-comedy-is-wrong-as-i-expected-anime-1st-promo-streamed|title={{'}}''My Youth Romantic Comedy Is Wrong as I Expected''{{'}} Anime's 1st Promo Streamed|date=2013-03-08|accessdate=2013-03-20|work=[[Anime News Network]]}}</ref> with an additional anime-original episode with writing by Wataru Watari following the series on June 27, 2013.<ref name=\"ANN1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2013-05-16/my-teen-romantic-comedy-snafu-gets-more-anime|title=''My Teen Romantic Comedy SNAFU'' Gets More Anime|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=2013-05-16|accessdate=2013-05-17}}</ref> The series was simulcast with English subtitles by [[Crunchyroll]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2013-04-09/crunchyroll-to-stream-my-teen-romantic-comedy-snafu-tv-anime|title=Crunchyroll to Stream {{'}}''My Teen Romantic Comedy SNAFU''{{'}} TV Anime|date=2013-04-09|accessdate=2013-04-09|work=[[Anime News Network]]}}</ref> An [[OVA]] episode on [[Blu-ray Disc]] was bundled with the limited edition of the video game, released on September 19, 2013.<ref name=\"ANN1\" /><ref name=\"ANN2\" />  The opening theme is {{Nihongo|\"Yukitoki\"|\u30e6\u30ad\u30c8\u30ad}} by [[Nagi Yanagi]] and the ending theme is \"Hello Alone\" by [[Saori Hayami]] and [[Nao T\u014dyama]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2013-03-30/my-youth-romantic-comedy-is-wrong-as-i-expected-anime-teaser-posted|title={{'}}''My Youth Romantic Comedy Is Wrong as I Expected''{{'}} Anime's Teaser Posted|date=2013-03-30|accessdate=2013-03-31|work=[[Anime News Network]]}}</ref> The anime has been licensed by [[Sentai Filmworks]] in North America and [[Madman Entertainment]] in Australia and New Zealand.<ref name=\"Official Sentai\">{{cite web|url=http://www.sentaifilmworks.com/shows/my-teen-romantic-comedy-snafu|title=''My Teen Romantic Comedy ~ SNAFU'' - Sentai Filmworks|publisher=[[Section23 Films#Sentai Filmworks|Sentai Filmworks]]|accessdate=September 25, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305202940/http://www.sentaifilmworks.com/shows/my-teen-romantic-comedy-snafu|archive-date=March 5, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Madman Entertainment Acquisitions From Supanova Pop Culture Expo - Gold Coast|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2013-04-21/madman-entertainment-acquisitions-from-supanova-pop-culture-expo-gold-coast|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=2013-04-21|accessdate=2013-04-25}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Sentai Filmworks Adds ''My Teen Romantic Comedy Snafu'' TV Anime|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2013-04-25/sentai-filmworks-adds-my-teen-romantic-comedy-snafu-tv-anime|publisher=Anime News Network|date=2013-04-25|accessdate=2013-04-25}}</ref>\n\nA second season was announced by [[Shogakukan]] in 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2014-04-16/my-teen-romantic-comedy-snafu-anime-gets-2nd-season|title=My Teen Romantic Comedy SNAFU Anime Gets 2nd Season|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=April 16, 2014|accessdate=April 17, 2014}}</ref> The season, titled \"Yahari Ore no Seishun Love Come wa Machigatteiru. Zoku\", is produced by [[Feel (animation studio)|Feel]] and directed by Kei Oikawa, with character designs by Yuichi Tanaka and series composition by Sh\u014dtar\u014d Suga.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2014-10-16/outbreak-company-oikawa-to-direct-my-teen-romantic-comedy-snafu-season-2-at-studio-feel/.80008|title=Outbreak Company's Oikawa to Direct My Teen Romantic Comedy SNAFU Season 2 at Studio feel.|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=October 16, 2014|accessdate=October 16, 2014}}</ref> It aired between April 3 and June 26, 2015. The opening theme is {{nihongo|\"Harumodoki\"|\u6625\u64ec\u304d|}} by Yanagi.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2015-02-22/nagi-yanagi-returns-to-perform-2nd-my-teen-romantic-comedy-snafu-season-opening/.85276|title='Nagi Yanagi Returns to Perform 2nd ''My Teen Romantic Comedy SNAFU'' Season's Opening|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=February 22, 2015|accessdate=April 4, 2015}}</ref> The ending theme is {{nihongo|\"Everyday World.\"|\u30a8\u30d6\u30ea\u30c7\u30a4\u30ef\u30fc\u30eb\u30c9|}} by Yukino Yukinoshita (Hayami) and Yui Yuigahama (T\u014dyama).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2015-03-09/saori-hayami-nao-toyama-return-to-sing-2nd-my-teen-romantic-comedy-snafu-season-ending/.85766|title=Saori Hayami, Nao T\u014dyama Return to Sing 2nd ''My Teen Romantic Comedy SNAFU'' Season's Ending|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=March 9, 2015|accessdate=April 4, 2015}}</ref> The second season has been licensed by Sentai Filmworks.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2015-04-04/sentai-filmworks-adds-pleiades-re-kan-snafu-too-hello-kinmoza-utapri-season-3-is-it-wrong-to-try-to-pick-up-girls-in-a-dungeon-food-wars/.86760|title=Sentai Filmworks Adds ''Pleiades'', ''Re-Kan'', ''Snafu Too'', ''Hello! Kinmoza'', ''UtaPri'' Season 3, ''Is It Wrong to Try to Pick Up Girls in a Dungeon?'', ''Food Wars''|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=April 4, 2014|accessdate=April 4, 2015}}</ref> An [[original video animation|OVA]] episode, titled {{nihongo|''Undoubtedly, Girls Are Made of Sugar, Spice, and Something Nice''|\u304d\u3063\u3068\u3001\u5973\u306e\u5b50\u306f\u304a\u7802\u7cd6\u3068\u30b9\u30d1\u30a4\u30b9\u3068\u7d20\u6575\u306a\u4f55\u304b\u3067\u3067\u304d\u3066\u3044\u308b|Kitto, Onna no Ko wa Osat\u014d to Spice to Suteki na Nanika de Dekiteiru}}, is bundled with the limited edition of the second video game, which was released on October 27, 2016.<ref name=\"OVA2\"/><ref name=\"Game2-Delay\"/> \n\nA third and final season was announced by Shogakukan on March 18, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-03-18/my-teen-romantic-comedy-snafu-tv-anime-gets-3rd-season/.144649|title=My Teen Romantic Comedy SNAFU TV Anime Gets 3rd Season|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=March 18, 2019|accessdate=March 18, 2019}}</ref>  Feel is returning to animate the third season,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-07-04/studio-feel-returns-for-my-teen-romantic-comedy-snafu-tv-anime-3rd-season-in-2020/.148647|title=Studio feel. Returns for My Teen Romantic Comedy SNAFU TV Anime's 3rd Season in 2020|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=July 4, 2019|accessdate=July 4, 2019}}</ref> with Kei Oikawa returning as director, Keiichir\u014d \u014cchi replacing Sh\u014dtar\u014d Suga as series composer, and Yuichi Tanaka returning as character designer. The season, titled \"Yahari Ore no Seishun Love Come wa Machigatteiru. Kan\", was set to premiere in April 9, 2020,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-11-10/my-teen-romantic-comedy-snafu-anime-season-3-video-reveals-cast-staff-title-spring-debut-and-teases-finale/.153126|title=My Teen Romantic Comedy SNAFU Anime Season 3's Video Reveals Cast, Staff, Title, Spring Debut & Teases Finale|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=November 10, 2019|accessdate=November 10, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/daily-briefs/2020-01-27/my-teen-romantic-comedy-snafu-anime-season-3-premieres-on-april-9/.155818|title=My Teen Romantic Comedy SNAFU Anime Season 3 Premieres on April 9|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=January 27, 2020|accessdate=January 27, 2020}}</ref> before the series was delayed due to the ongoing [[coronavirus outbreak]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Harding |first1=Daryl |title=My Teen Romantic Comedy SNAFU Climax TV Anime Broadcast Postponed Due to Coronavirus |url=https://www.crunchyroll.com/anime-news/2020/04/07/my-teen-romantic-comedy-snafu-climax-tv-anime-broadcast-postponed-due-to-coronavirus |website=Crunchyroll |accessdate=7 April 2020 |language=en-us}}</ref> The opening theme is by Yanagi, and the ending theme is by Yukino Yukinoshita (Hayami) and Yui Yuigahama (T\u014dyama).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2020-01-02/my-teen-romantic-comedy-snafu-anime-season-3-reveals-theme-songs/.154991|title=My Teen Romantic Comedy SNAFU Anime Season 3 Reveals Theme Songs|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=January 2, 2020|accessdate=January 27, 2020}}</ref> Sentai Filmworks licensed the third season globally excluding Asia.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sentaifilmworks.com/a/news/sentai-snaps-up-season-3-of-my-teen-romantic-comedy-snafu|title=SENTAI SNAPS UP SEASON 3 OF \u201cMY TEEN ROMANTIC COMEDY SNAFU\u201d|date=March 30, 2020|publisher=[[Sentai Filmworks]]|accessdate=March 31, 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn April 2, 2019, Sentai Filmworks confirmed on Twitter that the series will receive a dub.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/SentaiFilmworks/status/1112974197582696448|title=#AprilTruth: My Teen Romantic Comedy SNAFU dub is coming... (promise)|last=Filmworks|first=Sentai|date=2019-04-02|website=@SentaiFilmworks|language=en|access-date=2019-04-02}}</ref> On July 5, Sentai announced both seasons 1 and 2 will be dubbed.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-07-04/both-seasons-of-my-teen-romantic-comedy-snafu-anime-get-english-dub/.148616|title=Both Seasons of My Teen Romantic Comedy SNAFU Anime Get English Dub|website=Anime News Network|language=en|access-date=2019-07-05}}</ref>\n\n===Video games===\nA video game for [[PlayStation Vita]], titled {{Nihongo|''Yahari Game demo Ore no Seishun Rabu Kome wa Machigatteiru.''|\u3084\u306f\u308a\u30b2\u30fc\u30e0\u3067\u3082\u4ffa\u306e\u9752\u6625\u30e9\u30d6\u30b3\u30e1\u306f\u307e\u3061\u304c\u3063\u3066\u3044\u308b\u3002|lit. \"My Youth Romantic Comedy even in Game is Wrong As I Expected.\"}} was published by [[5pb.]] and released on September 19, 2013. Takuya Eguchi, Saori Hayami, and Nao T\u014dyama reprised their roles from the anime.<ref name=\"ANN2\">{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2013-06-05/my-teen-romantic-comedy-snafu-game-ova-to-ship-on-september-19|title=''My Teen Romantic Comedy SNAFU'' Game, OVA to Ship on September 19|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=June 5, 2013|accessdate=2013-06-07}}</ref> The limited edition was bundled with an OVA episode.<ref name=\"ANN1\" /> 5pb. developed a second video game for the series for the PlayStation Vita that adapted the second season of the anime television series.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2015-06-07/5pb-develops-my-teen-romantic-comedy-snafu-video-game-sequel/.89015|title=5pb. Develops ''My Teen Romantic Comedy SNAFU'' Video Game Sequel|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=June 7, 2015|accessdate=June 8, 2015}}</ref><ref>http://gematsu.com/2015/08/my-teen-romantic-comedy-snafu-too-game-confirmed-ps-vita</ref> It was released on October 27, 2016. Like the first game, the limited edition was bundled with an OVA episode.<ref name=\"OVA2\">{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-04-08/my-teen-romantic-comedy-snafu-too-ps-vita-game-to-bundle-original-anime-blu-ray/.100842|title=My Teen Romantic Comedy SNAFU TOO! PS Vita Game to Bundle Original Anime Blu-ray|date=April 8, 2016|website=[[Anime News Network]]|accessdate=April 8, 2016}}</ref> The release date of the second game was postponed from July 28, 2016 to October 27, 2016 on June 14, 2016.<ref name=\"Game2-Delay\">{{cite web|url=http://5pb.jp/games/topics/7513.html|title=PS Vita\u300e\u3084\u306f\u308a\u30b2\u30fc\u30e0\u3067\u3082\u4ffa\u306e\u9752\u6625\u30e9\u30d6\u30b3\u30e1\u306f\u307e\u3061\u304c\u3063\u3066\u3044\u308b\u3002\u7d9a\u300f\u767a\u58f2\u65e5\u5ef6\u671f\u306e\u304a\u8a6b\u3073\u3068\u304a\u77e5\u3089\u305b|date=June 14, 2016|accessdate=June 16, 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n''My Youth Romantic Comedy Is Wrong, As I Expected'' was chosen as the best light novel of Japan according to the online polls compiled by the ''[[Kono Light Novel ga Sugoi!]]'' annual guide book in 2014, 2015 and 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2014-11-12/my-teen-romantic-comedy-snafu-tops-kono-light-novel-ga-sugoi-list-for-2nd-straight-year/.80934|title=My Teen Romantic Comedy SNAFU Tops Kono Light Novel ga Sugoi! List for 2nd Straight Year|work=[[Anime News Network]]|date=November 11, 2014|accessdate=November 19, 2016}}</ref> Hachiman Hikigaya was elected the best male character in 2014, 2015 and 2016, Yukino Yukinoshita was elected the best female character in 2015 and Ponkan8, the series' artist, was chosen as the best illustrator in 2015 and 2016.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://gagagabunko.jp/specal/oregairu/ Light novel official website] {{in lang|ja}}\n* [http://www.tbs.co.jp/anime/oregairu Anime official website] {{in lang|ja}}\n* [http://5pb.jp/games/oregairu Video game official website] {{in lang|ja}}\n* {{ann|light novel|17263}}\n\n{{Gangan Comics manga franchises}}\n{{Monthly Sunday Gene-X}}\n{{Brain's Base}}\n{{Feel}}\n\n[[Category:2011 Japanese novels]]\n[[Category:2012 manga]]\n[[Category:2013 anime television series]]\n[[Category:2015 anime television series]]\n[[Category:Upcoming anime television series]]\n[[Category:Anime and manga based on light novels]]\n[[Category:Brain's Base]]\n[[Category:Feel (company)]]\n[[Category:Gagaga Bunko]]\n[[Category:Gangan Comics manga]]\n[[Category:Ichijinsha manga]]\n[[Category:Light novels]]\n[[Category:NBCUniversal Entertainment Japan]]\n[[Category:Romantic comedy anime and manga]]\n[[Category:School life in anime and manga]]\n[[Category:Seinen manga]]\n[[Category:Sentai Filmworks]]\n[[Category:Shogakukan franchises]]\n[[Category:Shogakukan manga]]\n[[Category:Slice of life anime and manga]]\n[[Category:Television programs based on light novels]]\n[[Category:Tokyo Broadcasting System shows]]\n[[Category:Yen Press titles]]\n", "name_user": "John of Reading", "label": "safe", "comment": "Typo/generalfixes, replaced: in April 9, 2020 \u2192 on April 9, 2020, surroudings \u2192 surroundings", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/My_Youth_Romantic_Comedy_Is_Wrong,_As_I_Expected"}
{"title_page": "Mamoiada", "text_new": "{{Infobox Italian comune\n| name                = Mamoiada\n| official_name       = Comune di Mamoiada\n| native_name         = Mamujada\n| image_skyline       = Mamoiada Panorama.jpg\n| imagesize           =  \n| image_alt           = \n| image_caption       =  \n| image_shield        = \n| shield_alt          = \n| image_map           = \n| map_alt             = \n| map_caption         = \n| pushpin_map         = Italy#Italy Sardinia\n| coordinates         = {{coord|40|13|N|9|17|E|type:city(2,582)_region:IT|display=inline,title}}\n| coordinates_footnotes = \n| region              = [[Sardinia]]\n| province            = [[Province of Nuoro]] (NU)\n| frazioni            = \n| mayor_party         = \n| mayor               = Luciano Barone \n| area_footnotes      = \n| area_total_km2      = 48.43\n| population_footnotes = \n| population_total    = 2547\n| population_as_of    = Dec. 2017\n| pop_density_footnotes = \n| population_demonym  = \n| elevation_footnotes = \n| elevation_m         = 650\n| saint               = \n| day                 = \n| postal_code         = 08024\n| area_code           = 0784\n| website             = \n| footnotes           = \n}}\n\n'''Mamoiada''' ({{lang-sc|Mamujada}}) is a ''[[comune]]'' (municipality) in the [[Province of Nuoro]] in the [[Italy|Italian]] region of [[Sardinia]], located about {{cvt|198|km|mi}} north of [[Cagliari]] and about {{cvt|16|km|mi|0}} southwest of [[Nuoro]]. As of 31 December 2017, it had a population of 2,547 and an area of {{convert|49.0|km2|mi2}}.<ref name=\"istat\">All demographics and other statistics: Italian statistical institute [[National Institute of Statistics (Italy)|Istat]].</ref>\n\n{{stack|\n[[File:Sardinia mamoiada perda pinta.jpg|thumb|Menhir of Perda Pinta]]\n[[File:Mamuthone e Issohadore di Mamoiada.jpg|thumb|The Mamuthones and the Issohadores (Traditional carnival mask from Mamoiada)]]\n}}\n\nThe town is known for its traditional carnival costumes, including distinctive masks worn by the ''mamuthones'' and ''issohadores''.<ref>[http://www.mamoiada.org :: Mamoiada.org, il pi\u00f9 grande portale sul paese dei Mamuthones...e non solo - Home ::<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref><ref>[https://www.cntraveler.com/story/a-pagan-exorcism-in-sardinia/amp ''A Pagan Exorcism in Sardinia'', CNTraveller.com]</ref> The local museum (museum of traditional mask of Mediterranean sea) houses some masks also from other part of Sardinia and Europe.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.museodellemaschere.it/english.htm |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2011-11-07 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111222064126/http://www.museodellemaschere.it/english.htm |archivedate=2011-12-22 }}</ref>\n\n==Economy==\n\n\nAs in other municipalities of Barbagia, the local economy is characterized by herding and viticulture, with high quality products. As of 2017, there were a hundred wineries of various sizes[6] with about 266 hectares of vineyards,[7] an area that in the past reached 400, mainly of cannonau. [8]\n\nSince the last years of the 20th century, tourism-related activities have also grown, especially in connection with cultural heritage and local events.\n\n==Culture ==\n\nHolidays and Folk Traditions Edit\nS'Antoni de su 'ohu, in January\nHarrasehare Mamujadinu, In February\nSantu Bustianu, in June\nMamuMask, International Mask Festival, end of June\nOn Carmu, in July\nLoret'Attesu, July\nSantu Cosomo and Damianu, late September\nSas Tappas in Mamujada, November\nMamuthones and Issohadores Edit\nMagnifying glass icon mgx2.svg The same topic in detail: Mamuthones and Mamoiada Carnival.\nThe mysterious Mamoiadin carnival - with ancestral origins - is among the oldest popular events in Sardinia. [4] [5] Its protagonists, the Mamuthones and the Issohadores, have long become the recognized symbol of the country. The Mamuthones, curved under the weight of the cowbells, and with their faces covered by a black wooden mask, move slowly in two parallel rows, giving a shoulder shot to shake the whole grille, with a very special clang. The Issohadores escort them with more agile steps and leaps, dressed in white mask and red bodice, and throw the snare (in the soha Mamoiadin dialect) suddenly capturing the young women as a sign of good health and fertility, or even the friend in a sign of chosen affection in the crowd, and then release it soon after. Once the landowners were caught, who, in order to pay off the honour reserved for them, then took the whole group home, offering wine and sweets. The issohador leader gives orders to the mamuthones and gives the rhythm to the dance. These masks make their first appearance on January 17 of each year on the occasion of the feast of St. Anthony Abbot. The festival is called St. Antoni and on 'ohu (\"St. Anthony of Fire\"), because, as in many Sardinian countries and other regions of the Mediterranean, numerous bonfires are lit around which the mysterious dances of the Mamuthones and Issohadores take place. The rite seems to have an apotropaic or propitiatory meaning. The noisy rattlesnake dance would serve to ward off evil and foster abundant agricultural years. Similar customs are found in other villages in various European countries.\n\nAlong with the masks of many European countries, Issohadores and Mamuthones can be seen at the recently expanded Museum of Mediterranean Masks. The Museum competes at the International Museum of Carnival and Mask of the Belgian city of Binche the greatest completeness of testimonies and finds on the carnival of the Mediterranean basin. The property organizes frequent international exchanges with museums, cultural institutions and associations working in this area.\n\n\nAbout Passu Torrau Edit\nOn Passu Torr\u00e0u, literally \"the step returned\", it is a dance, it is now widespread throughout Sardinia but seems to be native to the village of Mamoiada. In fact, in many recordings of many Sardinian players such as Mondo Vercellino, Mario and Francesco Bande is called \"Sa Mamojadina\".\n\n==Geography==\n\nMamoiada is located in the innermost part of Ollolai Barbagia, in a territory where numerous streams flow and flow, through land largely used for cultivation or grazing. The presence of these environmental resources has attracted human settlements since the Neolithic and pre-Neolithic, with a variety of significant archaeological and anthropological traces (from the votive stone, to the nuraghe, to menhir and dolmen, as far as the latter is concerned today there is no longer testimony, except the place names of the places where es. sa copreccada arose). It strikes Sa Perda Pint\u00e0 (i.e. \"the painted stone\", also known as Stele di Boeli), a 270 cm high slab marked with concentric circles and coppelles, all similar to similar slabs spread in the celt area (Scotland, Ireland, Corsica, Wales and Brittany).\n\nOther architectural legacies of later eras are mainly represented by churches. The church of Loreto, with a dome full of frescoes, was probably built around 1600. The sanctuary of saints Cosma and Damiano, which follows a much older structure, is located 5 km from the town on the Marghine Plateau, next to the road leading to Gavoi. The shrine is surrounded by about fifty houses for pilgrims (umbiss\u00ecas).\n\nThe altitude of the territory of the municipality is between 390 m and 1,048 m above sea level.\n\n==History== \n\nThe area was inhabited in pre-Nuragic, Nuragic (presence of domus de janas and some nuraghi) and Roman. Due to its strategic location at the north-south axis of Sardinia, along the Ulbiam-Caralis road, the village of Mamoiada was affected by a Roman military presence. The Su hastru ward has a name that follows what the Romans gave to their little pres\u00ecds (Castrum). The Roman presence is also evidenced by the fountain of Su hantaru vetzu (i.e. \"The Old Source\"), at the center of the ward of the same name.\n\nIn the Middle Ages he belonged to the Judge of Arborea and was part of the curator of the Barbagia of Ollolai. At the fall of the judge (1420) it passed under the rule of the Marquis of Oristano, and then passed under Aragonese domination (1478). In 1604 he was merged with the Duchy of Mandas, a fiefdom of the Maza. Dai Maza then moved to Tellez-Giron of Alcantara, to whom he was redeemed in 1839 with the suppression of the feudal system desired by the Savoy.\n\nMamoiada borders the following municipalities: [[Fonni]], [[Gavoi]], [[Nuoro]], [[Ollolai]], [[Orani, Italy|Orani]], [[Orgosolo]], [[Sarule]].\n\n== Demographic evolution ==\n{{Historical populations\n|align=none|cols=2\n|1861|1927\n|1871|2039\n|1881|2060\n|1901|2332\n|1911|2632\n|1921|2549\n|1931|2724\n|1936|2834\n|1951|3098\n|1961|3233\n|1971|2795\n|1981|2713\n|1991|2633\n|2001|2580\n|source=Data from ISTAT\n}}\n\n==References==\n{{commons category|Mamoiada}}\n<references/>\n\n{{clear}}\n{{Province of Nuoro}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Cities and towns in Sardinia]]\n\n\n{{Sardinia-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Italian comune\n| name                = Mamoiada\n| official_name       = Comune di Mamoiada\n| native_name         = Mamujada\n| image_skyline       = Mamoiada Panorama.jpg\n| imagesize           =  \n| image_alt           = \n| image_caption       =  \n| image_shield        = \n| shield_alt          = \n| image_map           = \n| map_alt             = \n| map_caption         = \n| pushpin_map         = Italy#Italy Sardinia\n| coordinates         = {{coord|40|13|N|9|17|E|type:city(2,582)_region:IT|display=inline,title}}\n| coordinates_footnotes = \n| region              = [[Sardinia]]\n| province            = [[Province of Nuoro]] (NU)\n| frazioni            = \n| mayor_party         = \n| mayor               = Graziano Deiana\n| area_footnotes      = \n| area_total_km2      = 48.43\n| population_footnotes = \n| population_total    = 2582\n| population_as_of    = Dec. 2004\n| pop_density_footnotes = \n| population_demonym  = \n| elevation_footnotes = \n| elevation_m         = 650\n| saint               = \n| day                 = \n| postal_code         = 08024\n| area_code           = 0784\n| website             = \n| footnotes           = \n}}\n\n'''Mamoiada''' ({{lang-sc|Mamujada}}) is a ''[[comune]]'' (municipality) in the [[Province of Nuoro]] in the [[Italy|Italian]] region of [[Sardinia]], located about {{cvt|110|km|mi}} north of [[Cagliari]] and about {{cvt|12|km|mi|0}} southwest of [[Nuoro]]. As of 31 December 2004, it had a population of 2,582 and an area of {{convert|49.0|km2|mi2}}.<ref name=\"istat\">All demographics and other statistics: Italian statistical institute [[National Institute of Statistics (Italy)|Istat]].</ref>\n\n{{stack|\n[[File:Sardinia mamoiada perda pinta.jpg|thumb|Menhir of Perda Pinta]]\n[[File:Mamuthone e Issohadore di Mamoiada.jpg|thumb|The Mamuthones and the Issohadores (Traditional carnival mask from Mamoiada)]]\n}}\n\nThe town is known for its traditional carnival costumes, including distinctive masks worn by the ''mamuthones'' and ''issohadores''.<ref>[http://www.mamoiada.org :: Mamoiada.org, il pi\u00f9 grande portale sul paese dei Mamuthones...e non solo - Home ::<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref><ref>[https://www.cntraveler.com/story/a-pagan-exorcism-in-sardinia/amp ''A Pagan Exorcism in Sardinia'', CNTraveller.com]</ref> The local museum houses some masks also from other part of Sardinia and Europe.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.museodellemaschere.it/english.htm |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2011-11-07 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111222064126/http://www.museodellemaschere.it/english.htm |archivedate=2011-12-22 }}</ref>\n\nMamoiada borders the following municipalities: [[Fonni]], [[Gavoi]], [[Nuoro]], [[Ollolai]], [[Orani, Italy|Orani]], [[Orgosolo]], [[Sarule]].\n\n== Demographic evolution ==\n{{Historical populations\n|align=none|cols=2\n|1861|1927\n|1871|2039\n|1881|2060\n|1901|2332\n|1911|2632\n|1921|2549\n|1931|2724\n|1936|2834\n|1951|3098\n|1961|3233\n|1971|2795\n|1981|2713\n|1991|2633\n|2001|2580\n|source=Data from ISTAT\n}}\n\n==References==\n{{commons category|Mamoiada}}\n<references/>\n\n{{clear}}\n{{Province of Nuoro}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Cities and towns in Sardinia]]\n\n\n{{Sardinia-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "82.23.122.6", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mamoiada"}
{"title_page": "Gerhard Vollmer", "text_new": "{{BLP sources|date=September 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n'''Gerhard Vollmer''' (born 17 November 1943) is a German [[physicist]] and [[philosopher]]. He is perhaps best known for his development of an [[Evolutionary Epistemology|evolutionary theory of knowledge]].<ref>{{cite book|title=Die Geschichte Gottes und die Geschichte der Natur - eine Familien\u00e4hnlichkeit? |trans-title=The history of God and the history of nature - a family likeness? |language=German |first=Dieter |last=Weber |page=10 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=bu-ITtQfF84C&pg=PA323&dq=%22Gerhard+Vollmer%22&hl=en&sa=X&ei=-zITVJioCa6f7Abi3YGIDQ&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=%22Gerhard%20Vollmer%22&f=false |publisher=LIT Verlag |location=M\u00fcnster |year=2000 |isbn=9783825837372}}</ref>\n\n==Life==\nVollmer was born in [[Speyer]]. He studied in [[Munich]], [[Berlin]], [[Hamburg]] and [[Freiburg]]. After finishing his degree in physics in 1968 he studied [[philosophy]] and [[linguistics]] in Freiburg. He worked as a trainee in ''Deutschen Elektronen-Synchrotron'' (DESY) in Hamburg. In Freiburg he attained a doctorate (1971) in [[theoretical physics]]. He stayed here after completing a year's stint as a research assistant in Montreal in 1975. In 1974, Vollmer attained an additional doctorate in philosophy.\n\nFrom 1975 Vollmer taught at the [[Leibniz University Hannover]]. From 1981 he lectured on the [[Philosophy of biology|Philosophy of Biology]] at the [[University of Giessen]]. From 1991 he has taught philosophy at the [[TU Braunschweig]]. He holds lectures and classes in [[logic]], [[epistemology]] and [[philosophy of science]], [[natural philosophy]], and [[artificial intelligence]]. He has also worked on [[evolutionary ethics]], which he says consists of attempts to add evolutionary points of view to philosophical ethics.<ref>{{cite book|title=Evolution\u00e4re Ethik? |trans-title=Evolutionary ethics? |language=German |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=dLuVl9WdpNIC&pg=PA161&dq=%22Gerhard+Vollmer%22&hl=en&sa=X&ei=-zITVJioCa6f7Abi3YGIDQ&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=%22Gerhard%20Vollmer%22&f=false |first=Bernd |last=Gr\u00e4frath |publisher=Walter de Gruyter |year=1997 |isbn=9783110153927 |page=161}}</ref>\n\n==Honours and associations==\nIn 1963 he was awarded the [[Friedrich Magnus Schwerd|Magnus Schwerd]] Prize for outstanding achievements in mathematics at school.\n \nVollmer became a member in 1998 of the [[German Academy of Sciences Leopoldina|Leopoldina Academy of Sciences Halle]]. He is a member of '''Giordano Bruno Foundation''' (a society dedicated to a sort of evolutionary humanism, weblink below) and (in 2001) was elected to the learned society, '''Braunschweig Sciences Society''' (Braunschweigische Wissenschaftliche Gesellschaft). On his 60th birthday in 2003 a [[Festschrift]] was produced in his honour called \"Cold-blooded: Philosophy from a rational standpoint\" (\"''Kaltbl\u00fctig. Philosophie von einem rationalen Standpunkt''\" edited by Wolfgang Buschlinger and [[Christoph Luetge| Christoph L\u00fctge]], published by Hirzel Verlag, Stuttgart).\n\nIn 2004 he received the [[Eduard Rhein|''Eduard Rhein Foundation Cultural Prize'']] for having laid down the \u201c''foundation of an evolutionary theory of knowledge and for his outstanding achievement in bridging natural sciences and the social and humanistic disciplines''\u201d.\n\nHe is one of the editors of the periodical ''Aufkl\u00e4rung und Kritik''. He is a member of the Science Advisory Committee of the [[Gesellschaft zur wissenschaftlichen Untersuchung von Parawissenschaften]] (GWUP), a German-speaking organisation supporting [[scientific skepticism]]. Vollmer is also a member of the [[Brights movement]].\n\n==Publications==\n* ''Evolution\u00e4re Erkenntnistheorie'' (Evolutionary epistemology) (1975, 8. Aufl. 2002)\n* ''Was k\u00f6nnen wir wissen?'' (What can we know?) (2 Bde. 2. Aufl. 1988)\n* ''Wissenschaftstheorie im Einsatz'' (Philosophy of Science in practice) (1993)\n* ''Auf der Suche nach der Ordnung'' (In search of order) (1995)\n* ''Biophilosophie'' (Philosophy of Biology) (1995)\n* ''Wieso k\u00f6nnen wir die Welt erkennen''? (How can we grasp the nature of the world?) (2002)\n\nThere is a chapter by Vollmer in English in \n* Bartley, W W. and Radnitzky, Gerard (eds) ''Evolutionary epistemology, rationality and the sociology of knowledge''. La Salle, IL : Open Court, 1987. {{ISBN|0-8126-9038-9}} ; {{ISBN|0-8126-9039-7}} (pbk)\n* H\u00f6sle, Vittorio and Illies, Christian (eds) ''Darwinism and philosophy '' University of Notre Dame Press, 2005. {{ISBN|0-268-03072-3}} (hbk) ; {{ISBN|0-268-03073-1}} (pbk) (Chapter 13. How Is It That We Can Know This World? New Arguments in Evolutionary Epistemology, by G Vollmer)\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://www.tu-braunschweig.de/philosophie/personen/ehemalige/vollmer Gerhard Vollmer] at TU Braunschweig\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Vollmer, Gerhard}}\n[[Category:1943 births]]\n[[Category:German philosophers]]\n[[Category:German physicists]]\n[[Category:German skeptics]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Braunschweig University of Technology faculty]]\n[[Category:German male writers]]\n", "text_old": "{{BLP sources|date=September 2014}}\n'''Gerhard Vollmer''' (born 17 November 1943) is a German [[physicist]] and [[philosopher]]. He is perhaps best known for his development of an [[Evolutionary Epistemology|evolutionary theory of knowledge]].<ref>{{cite book|title=Die Geschichte Gottes und die Geschichte der Natur - eine Familien\u00e4hnlichkeit? |trans-title=The history of God and the history of nature - a family likeness? |language=German |first=Dieter |last=Weber |page=10 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=bu-ITtQfF84C&pg=PA323&dq=%22Gerhard+Vollmer%22&hl=en&sa=X&ei=-zITVJioCa6f7Abi3YGIDQ&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=%22Gerhard%20Vollmer%22&f=false |publisher=LIT Verlag |location=M\u00fcnster |year=2000 |isbn=9783825837372}}</ref>\n\n==Life==\nVollmer was born in [[Speyer]]. He studied in [[Munich]], [[Berlin]], [[Hamburg]] and [[Freiburg]]. After finishing his degree in physics in 1968 he studied [[philosophy]] and [[linguistics]] in Freiburg. He worked as a trainee in ''Deutschen Elektronen-Synchrotron'' (DESY) in Hamburg. In Freiburg he attained a doctorate (1971) in [[theoretical physics]]. He stayed here after completing a year's stint as a research assistant in Montreal in 1975. In 1974, Vollmer attained an additional doctorate in philosophy.\n\nFrom 1975 Vollmer taught at the [[Leibniz University Hannover]]. From 1981 he lectured on the [[Philosophy of biology|Philosophy of Biology]] at the [[University of Giessen]]. From 1991 he has taught philosophy at the [[TU Braunschweig]]. He holds lectures and classes in [[logic]], [[epistemology]] and [[philosophy of science]], [[natural philosophy]], and [[artificial intelligence]]. He has also worked on [[evolutionary ethics]], which he says consists of attempts to add evolutionary points of view to philosophical ethics.<ref>{{cite book|title=Evolution\u00e4re Ethik? |trans-title=Evolutionary ethics? |language=German |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=dLuVl9WdpNIC&pg=PA161&dq=%22Gerhard+Vollmer%22&hl=en&sa=X&ei=-zITVJioCa6f7Abi3YGIDQ&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=%22Gerhard%20Vollmer%22&f=false |first=Bernd |last=Gr\u00e4frath |publisher=Walter de Gruyter |year=1997 |isbn=9783110153927 |page=161}}</ref>\n\n==Honours and associations==\nIn 1963 he was awarded the [[Friedrich Magnus Schwerd|Magnus Schwerd]] Prize for outstanding achievements in mathematics at school.\n \nVollmer became a member in 1998 of the [[German Academy of Sciences Leopoldina|Leopoldina Academy of Sciences Halle]]. He is a member of '''Giordano Bruno Foundation''' (a society dedicated to a sort of evolutionary humanism, weblink below) and (in 2001) was elected to the learned society, '''Braunschweig Sciences Society''' (Braunschweigische Wissenschaftliche Gesellschaft). On his 60th birthday in 2003 a [[Festschrift]] was produced in his honour called \"Cold-blooded: Philosophy from a rational standpoint\" (\"''Kaltbl\u00fctig. Philosophie von einem rationalen Standpunkt''\" edited by Wolfgang Buschlinger and [[Christoph Luetge| Christoph L\u00fctge]], published by Hirzel Verlag, Stuttgart).\n\nIn 2004 he received the [[Eduard Rhein|''Eduard Rhein Foundation Cultural Prize'']] for having laid down the \u201c''foundation of an evolutionary theory of knowledge and for his outstanding achievement in bridging natural sciences and the social and humanistic disciplines''\u201d.\n\nHe is one of the editors of the periodical ''Aufkl\u00e4rung und Kritik''. He is a member of the Science Advisory Committee of the [[Gesellschaft zur wissenschaftlichen Untersuchung von Parawissenschaften]] (GWUP), a German-speaking organisation supporting [[scientific skepticism]]. Vollmer is also a member of the [[Brights movement]].\n\n==Publications==\n* ''Evolution\u00e4re Erkenntnistheorie'' (Evolutionary epistemology) (1975, 8. Aufl. 2002)\n* ''Was k\u00f6nnen wir wissen?'' (What can we know?) (2 Bde. 2. Aufl. 1988)\n* ''Wissenschaftstheorie im Einsatz'' (Philosophy of Science in practice) (1993)\n* ''Auf der Suche nach der Ordnung'' (In search of order) (1995)\n* ''Biophilosophie'' (Philosophy of Biology) (1995)\n* ''Wieso k\u00f6nnen wir die Welt erkennen''? (How can we grasp the nature of the world?) (2002)\n\nThere is a chapter by Vollmer in English in \n* Bartley, W W. and Radnitzky, Gerard (eds) ''Evolutionary epistemology, rationality and the sociology of knowledge''. La Salle, IL : Open Court, 1987. {{ISBN|0-8126-9038-9}} ; {{ISBN|0-8126-9039-7}} (pbk)\n* H\u00f6sle, Vittorio and Illies, Christian (eds) ''Darwinism and philosophy '' University of Notre Dame Press, 2005. {{ISBN|0-268-03072-3}} (hbk) ; {{ISBN|0-268-03073-1}} (pbk) (Chapter 13. How Is It That We Can Know This World? New Arguments in Evolutionary Epistemology, by G Vollmer)\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://www.tu-braunschweig.de/philosophie/personen/ehemalige/vollmer Gerhard Vollmer] at TU Braunschweig\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Vollmer, Gerhard}}\n[[Category:1943 births]]\n[[Category:German philosophers]]\n[[Category:German physicists]]\n[[Category:German skeptics]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Braunschweig University of Technology faculty]]\n[[Category:German male writers]]\n", "name_user": "Robby.is.on", "label": "safe", "comment": "Date formats perMOS:DATEFORMATbyscript.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gerhard_Vollmer"}
